250
00:26:56.374 --> 00:26:58.772
Carol. are we seeing
you here next month?

251
00:26:58.801 --> 00:27:01.850
- Not likely.
- What. you gonna get another haircut?

252
00:27:01.895 --> 00:27:05.511
Listen. fur-face. I'm
covering a lot of territory.

253
00:27:05.536 --> 00:27:07.411
The things that are
happening on Earth are

254
00:27:07.436 --> 00:27:10.302
happening everywhere. on
thousands of planets.

255
00:27:11.030 --> 00:27:12.998
That's a good point.
That's a good point.

256
00:27:13.670 --> 00:27:16.351
So you might not see
me for a long time.

257
00:27:16.572 --> 00:27:18.513
All right. Uh. well...

258
00:27:19.153 --> 00:27:23.457
This channel is always active.
So. anything goes sideways...

259
00:27:23.528 --> 00:27:25.949
Anyone's making trouble
where they shouldn't...

260
00:27:26.215 --> 00:27:29.097
- Comes through me.
- Okay.

261
00:27:29.113 --> 00:27:30.113
All right.

262
00:27:31.235 --> 00:27:32.535
Good luck.

263
00:27:40.874 --> 00:27:43.218
- Where are you?
- Mexico.

264
00:27:43.271 --> 00:27:46.226
The federales found a
room full of bodies.

265
00:27:46.468 --> 00:27:50.053
Looks like a bunch of cartel guys. Never
even had the chance to get their guns off.

266
00:27:50.124 --> 00:27:53.491
- It's probably a rival gang...
- Except it isn't.

267
00:27:53.516 --> 00:27:55.896
It's definitely Barton.

268
00:27:56.039 --> 00:28:00.406
What he's done here. what he's
been doing for the last few years.

269
00:28:01.998 --> 00:28:04.060
I mean. the scene
that he left...

270
00:28:04.630 --> 00:28:07.935
I gotta tell you. there's a part of
me that doesn't even wanna find him.

271
00:28:13.767 --> 00:28:16.102
Will you find out where
he's going next?

272
00:28:20.064 --> 00:28:21.064
Nat...

273
00:28:22.624 --> 00:28:23.829
Please.

274
00:28:26.460 --> 00:28:27.460
Okay.

275
00:28:36.273 --> 00:28:40.343
You know I'd offer to clip your dinner
but you seem pretty miserable already.

276
00:28:44.110 --> 00:28:45.499
You here to do your laundry?

277
00:28:45.524 --> 00:28:47.445
And to see a friend.

278
00:28:48.329 --> 00:28:50.266
Clearly. your friend is fine.

279
00:28:53.599 --> 00:28:56.222
You know I saw a pod of whales
when I was coming up the bridge.

280
00:28:56.247 --> 00:28:59.364
- In the Hudson?
- There's fewer ships. cleaner water.

281
00:28:59.372 --> 00:29:03.426
You know. if you're about to tell
me to look on the bright side...

282
00:29:03.971 --> 00:29:04.971
Um...

283
00:29:06.080 --> 00:29:09.838
I'm about to hit you in the head
with a peanut butter sandwich.

284
00:29:11.737 --> 00:29:14.572
Sorry. Force of habit.

285
00:29:28.425 --> 00:29:32.635
You know I keep telling everybody
they should move on and... grow.

286
00:29:34.783 --> 00:29:35.915
Some do.

287
00:29:39.486 --> 00:29:40.657
But not us.

288
00:29:41.523 --> 00:29:45.843
- If I move on. who does this?
- Maybe it doesn't need to be done.

289
00:29:50.430 --> 00:29:52.445
I used to have nothing.

290
00:29:53.594 --> 00:29:55.672
And then I got this.

291
00:29:57.969 --> 00:29:59.258
This job.

292
00:30:02.119 --> 00:30:03.414
This family.

293
00:30:07.596 --> 00:30:11.275
And I was... I was
better because of it.

294
00:30:17.784 --> 00:30:19.096
And even though...

295
00:30:20.161 --> 00:30:21.629
they're gone...

296
00:30:25.278 --> 00:30:27.559
Now. I'm still
trying to be better.

297
00:30:30.875 --> 00:30:32.921
I think we both
need to get a life.

298
00:30:35.766 --> 00:30:37.007
You first.

299
00:30:42.195 --> 00:30:43.616
Oh... Hi. Hi!

300
00:30:43.640 --> 00:30:46.582
Is anyone home?
This is Scott Lang.

301
00:30:46.607 --> 00:30:51.255
We met a few years ago. at the airport?
In Germany?

302
00:30:51.287 --> 00:30:54.146
I got really big and
I had my mask on.

303
00:30:54.171 --> 00:30:56.091
- You wouldn't recognize me.
- Is this an old message?

304
00:30:56.116 --> 00:30:59.046
Ant-Man? Ant-Man. I
know you know that.

305
00:30:59.132 --> 00:31:00.155
It's the front gate.

306
00:31:00.186 --> 00:31:01.986
I need to talk to you guys.

307
00:31:07.850 --> 00:31:08.850
Scott.

308
00:31:10.193 --> 00:31:12.200
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

309
00:31:13.864 --> 00:31:16.419
Have either of you guys ever
studied quantum physics?

310
00:31:16.748 --> 00:31:18.864
Only in mid-conversation.

311
00:31:19.052 --> 00:31:20.052
Alright. So...

312
00:31:21.155 --> 00:31:25.810
Five years ago. right before...
Thanos.

313
00:31:25.913 --> 00:31:28.147
I was in a place called
the quantum realm.

314
00:31:28.319 --> 00:31:31.186
The quantum realm is like its
own microscopic universe.

315
00:31:31.211 --> 00:31:34.750
To get in there. you have to be
incredibly small. Hope. she's my...

316
00:31:36.586 --> 00:31:38.102
She... she was my...

317
00:31:40.141 --> 00:31:43.843
She was supposed to pull me out.
And then Thanos happened. and

318
00:31:43.868 --> 00:31:47.539
- I got stuck in there.
- Sorry. That must've been a long 5 years.

319
00:31:47.564 --> 00:31:50.235
Yeah. but that's just it.
It wasn't.

320
00:31:50.243 --> 00:31:51.977
For me it was five hours.

321
00:31:52.002 --> 00:31:54.565
See. the rules of the quantum realm
aren't like they are up here.

322
00:31:54.611 --> 00:31:59.040
Everything is unpredictable. Is that
anybody's sandwich? I'm starving.

323
00:31:59.353 --> 00:32:00.353
Scott.

324
00:32:00.439 --> 00:32:02.329
What are you talking about?

325
00:32:02.421 --> 00:32:03.421
So...

326
00:32:04.538 --> 00:32:06.319
What I'm saying is...

327
00:32:07.036 --> 00:32:09.387
Time works differently
in the quantum realm.

328
00:32:09.475 --> 00:32:11.653
The only problem is right now. we
don't have a way to navigate it.

329
00:32:11.694 --> 00:32:13.037
But what if we did?

330
00:32:13.085 --> 00:32:16.810
I can't stop thinking about it. What
if we could somehow control the chaos.

331
00:32:16.835 --> 00:32:20.317
and we could navigate it? What if
there was a way that we can enter

332
00:32:20.342 --> 00:32:22.787
the quantum realm at a certain
point in time but then

333
00:32:22.812 --> 00:32:25.912
exit the quantum realm at
another point in time? Like...

334
00:32:27.191 --> 00:32:28.792
Like before Thanos.

335
00:32:28.995 --> 00:32:31.281
Wait. are you talking
about a time machine?

336
00:32:31.306 --> 00:32:34.426
No. No. of course not.
No. not a time machine.

337
00:32:34.575 --> 00:32:36.630
It's more like a...

338
00:32:37.862 --> 00:32:41.369
Yeah. a time machine. I know it's crazy.
It's crazy.

339
00:32:41.932 --> 00:32:45.299
But I can't stop thinking about it.
There's gotta be...

340
00:32:45.674 --> 00:32:48.513
Some wa... It's crazy.

341
00:32:48.538 --> 00:32:52.483
I get e-mails from a raccoon. So.
nothing sounds crazy anymore.

342
00:32:53.288 --> 00:32:55.366
So who do we talk to about this?

343
00:33:13.418 --> 00:33:14.418
Chow-time!

344
00:33:16.880 --> 00:33:17.880
Morgoona.

345
00:33:22.372 --> 00:33:24.583
Morgan H. Stark.
Want some lunch?

346
00:33:24.763 --> 00:33:27.661
- Define lunch or be disintegrated.
- Okay.

347
00:33:28.669 --> 00:33:30.019
You should not be
wearing that. okay?

348
00:33:30.044 --> 00:33:32.925
That is part of a special anniversary
gift I'm making for Mom.

349
00:33:36.316 --> 00:33:38.518
There you go. Are you
thinking about lunch?

350
00:33:39.034 --> 00:33:41.190
Want a handful of crickets?

351
00:33:41.253 --> 00:33:43.095
- No.
- That's what you want.

352
00:33:43.120 --> 00:33:46.534
- How did you find this?
- Garage.

353
00:33:46.570 --> 00:33:47.343
Really?

354
00:33:47.367 --> 00:33:49.726
- Were you looking for it?
- No.

355
00:33:50.249 --> 00:33:51.920
I found it. though.

356
00:33:52.209 --> 00:33:55.435
You like going to the garage. huh?
So does Daddy.

357
00:33:56.467 --> 00:33:59.415
It's fine actually. Mom never
wears anything I wear.

358
00:34:20.860 --> 00:34:23.193
Now. we know what
it sounds like...

359
00:34:23.266 --> 00:34:25.218
Tony after everything you've seen.
is anything really impossible...

360
00:34:25.242 --> 00:34:27.631
Quantum fluctuation messes
with the Planck scale.

361
00:34:27.656 --> 00:34:30.664
which then triggers the Deutsch
proposition. Can we agree on that?

362
00:34:30.820 --> 00:34:31.820
Thank you.

363
00:34:31.859 --> 00:34:34.515
In Layman's terms. it means
you're not coming home.

364
00:34:34.540 --> 00:34:35.540
- I did.
- No.

365
00:34:35.578 --> 00:34:37.574
You accidentally survived. It's a---

366
00:34:37.621 --> 00:34:40.129
It's a billion-to-one
cosmic fluke.

367
00:34:40.197 --> 00:34:41.964
And now you wanna pull a...

368
00:34:42.119 --> 00:34:43.587
What do you call it?

369
00:34:45.305 --> 00:34:48.015
- A time heist?
- Yeah. Time heist.

370
00:34:48.289 --> 00:34:50.456
Of course. Why didn't we
think of this before?

371
00:34:50.481 --> 00:34:52.972
Oh! Because it's laughable?
Because it's a pipedream?

372
00:34:52.997 --> 00:34:56.442
The stones are in the past. We
can go back and we can get them.

373
00:34:56.467 --> 00:34:58.973
We can snap our own fingers.
We can bring everybody back.

374
00:34:58.998 --> 00:35:01.139
Or screw it up worse than
he already has. right?

375
00:35:01.179 --> 00:35:02.404
I don't believe we would.

376
00:35:02.529 --> 00:35:05.841
Gotta say this. Sometimes. I
miss that giddy optimism.

377
00:35:06.121 --> 00:35:09.136
However. high hopes won't
help if there's no logical.

378
00:35:09.161 --> 00:35:13.457
tangible. way for me to safely
execute said time heist.

379
00:35:13.950 --> 00:35:16.577
I believe the most likely outcome
will be our collective demise.

380
00:35:16.602 --> 00:35:19.609
Not if we strictly follow
the rules of time travel.

381
00:35:19.836 --> 00:35:23.781
That means no talking to our past selves.
no betting on sporting events...

382
00:35:23.813 --> 00:35:26.343
I'm gonna stop you
right there. Scott.

383
00:35:26.899 --> 00:35:28.968
Are you seriously telling
me that your plan to

384
00:35:28.993 --> 00:35:32.093
save the universe is based
on Back to the Future?

385
00:35:34.036 --> 00:35:36.114
- No.
- Good. You had me worried there.

386
00:35:36.136 --> 00:35:39.409
'Cause that'd be horseshit. That's
not how quantum physics works.

387
00:35:39.662 --> 00:35:40.662
Tony...

388
00:35:42.662 --> 00:35:44.552
We have to take a stand.

389
00:35:44.951 --> 00:35:47.701
We did stand. And
yet. here we are.

390
00:35:49.138 --> 00:35:52.904
I know you got a lot on the line.
You got a wife. a daughter.

391
00:35:53.740 --> 00:35:57.990
But I lost someone very important to me.
A lot of people did.

392
00:35:58.083 --> 00:36:02.464
And now. now. we have a chance to bring
her back. To bring everyone back.

393
00:36:02.489 --> 00:36:04.090
And you're telling me
that you won't even...

394
00:36:04.115 --> 00:36:06.122
That's right. Scott.
I won't. Leave it.

395
00:36:07.739 --> 00:36:09.348
Got a kid.

396
00:36:11.192 --> 00:36:13.442
Mommy told me to
come and save you.

397
00:36:13.467 --> 00:36:16.113
Good job. I'm saved.

398
00:36:16.706 --> 00:36:18.855
I wish you'd come here to
ask me something else.

399
00:36:18.871 --> 00:36:21.784
Anything else. Honestly. I
missed you guys. it was...

400
00:36:21.863 --> 00:36:24.972
- Oh. and table's set for six.
- Tony. I get it.

401
00:36:25.089 --> 00:36:27.479
And I'm happy for you.
I really am.

402
00:36:28.097 --> 00:36:30.057
But this is a second chance.

403
00:36:30.355 --> 00:36:32.792
I got my second chance
right here. Cap.

404
00:36:32.891 --> 00:36:35.008
I can't roll the dice again.

405
00:36:36.497 --> 00:36:39.200
If you don't talk shop.
you can stay for lunch.

406
00:36:41.951 --> 00:36:44.522
- He's scared.
- He's not wrong.

407
00:36:44.740 --> 00:36:46.966
Yeah. but I mean.
what are we gonna do?

408
00:36:47.099 --> 00:36:49.231
We need him. What.
are we gonna stop?

409
00:36:49.256 --> 00:36:51.162
No. I wanna do it right.

410
00:36:54.433 --> 00:36:56.613
We're gonna need a
really big brain.

411
00:36:56.964 --> 00:36:58.690
Bigger than his?

412
00:36:59.041 --> 00:37:01.869
Come on. I feel like I'm the only
one eating. Try some of that.

413
00:37:01.894 --> 00:37:03.127
Have some eggs.

414
00:37:03.393 --> 00:37:04.674
I'm so confused.

415
00:37:04.702 --> 00:37:07.350
- These are confusing times.
- Right. No. no...

416
00:37:07.374 --> 00:37:10.256
- That's not what I meant. I...
- No. I get it.

417
00:37:10.281 --> 00:37:13.687
I'm kidding! I know. It's crazy.

418
00:37:13.812 --> 00:37:18.082
- I'm wearing shirts now.
- Yeah! How? Why?

419
00:37:18.222 --> 00:37:20.770
Five years ago we
got our asses beat.

420
00:37:21.239 --> 00:37:24.146
Except it was worse for me.
Because I lost twice.

421
00:37:24.389 --> 00:37:28.488
First. Hulk lost. Then Banner lost.
Then. we all lost.

422
00:37:28.513 --> 00:37:31.357
- No one blamed you. Bruce.
- I did.

423
00:37:32.923 --> 00:37:34.791
For years I've been
treating the Hulk like he's

424
00:37:34.816 --> 00:37:37.252
some kind of disease.
something to get rid of.

425
00:37:38.026 --> 00:37:40.908
But then I started looking
at him as the cure.

426
00:37:40.975 --> 00:37:46.029
Eighteen months in a gamma lab. I put
the brains and the brawn together.

427
00:37:46.170 --> 00:37:49.943
And now look at me.
Best of both worlds.

428
00:37:50.149 --> 00:37:52.227
- Excuse me. Mr. Hulk?
- Yes?

429
00:37:52.252 --> 00:37:55.861
- Can we get a photo?
- 100%. little person.

430
00:37:55.909 --> 00:37:58.705
Come on. step on up. You mind?

431
00:37:58.730 --> 00:37:59.730
Oh.

432
00:38:00.411 --> 00:38:03.036
- Say "green."
- Green.

433
00:38:03.061 --> 00:38:04.715
Greeeen.

434
00:38:04.740 --> 00:38:07.443
- Did you get that?
- That's good.

435
00:38:07.771 --> 00:38:10.779
Don't you wanna grab one with me?
I'm Ant-Man.

436
00:38:13.552 --> 00:38:15.206
They're Hulk fans.
They don't know Ant-Man.

437
00:38:15.231 --> 00:38:17.417
- Nobody does.
- Wait. no. no. he wants to...

438
00:38:17.442 --> 00:38:19.964
You want to take a
picture with him. right?

439
00:38:19.989 --> 00:38:22.106
He's even saying no he doesn't.
I get it.

440
00:38:22.131 --> 00:38:25.090
I don't want it either. I don't
want a picture with them.

441
00:38:25.092 --> 00:38:26.998
- He's gonna feel bad.
- Sorry.

442
00:38:27.029 --> 00:38:29.373
- They said they'd do it.
- I don't want it anymore.

443
00:38:29.398 --> 00:38:31.904
- You'd feel bad...
- Take the goddamn phone.

444
00:38:33.021 --> 00:38:33.954
Thank you. Mr. Hulk.

445
00:38:33.979 --> 00:38:36.256
No. it's great. kids.
Thank you very much.

446
00:38:36.569 --> 00:38:38.725
- Hulk out!
- Bruce.

447
00:38:39.500 --> 00:38:40.951
- Dab.
- Bruce.

448
00:38:40.976 --> 00:38:43.679
Listen to your Mom.
She knows better.

449
00:38:43.704 --> 00:38:46.671
- About we were saying...
- Right.

450
00:38:48.582 --> 00:38:51.285
The whole time travel do-over?

451
00:38:52.698 --> 00:38:55.878
Guys. it's outside of
my area of expertise.

452
00:38:56.957 --> 00:38:58.839
Well. you pulled this off.

453
00:38:59.191 --> 00:39:02.644
I remember a time when that
seemed pretty impossible. too.

454
00:39:36.149 --> 00:39:38.852
Look at a mod inspiration.
let me see what checks out.

455
00:39:39.138 --> 00:39:43.005
So. recommend one last sim before
we pack it in for the night.

456
00:39:43.029 --> 00:39:47.630
This time. in the shape of a
mobius strip. inverted. Please?

457
00:39:47.655 --> 00:39:49.287
Processing...

458
00:39:52.451 --> 00:39:56.784
Give me that eigenvalue. That. particle
factoring. and spectral decomp.

459
00:39:56.809 --> 00:39:59.505
- Gotta take a second.
- Just a moment.

460
00:39:59.926 --> 00:40:03.152
And don't worry if it doesn't pan out.
I'm just kinda...

461
00:40:04.315 --> 00:40:06.424
Model rendered.

462
00:40:17.669 --> 00:40:18.669
Shit!

463
00:40:19.019 --> 00:40:20.019
Shit!

464
00:40:24.234 --> 00:40:26.140
What are you doing
up. Little Miss?

465
00:40:26.195 --> 00:40:27.999
- Shit.
- No. We don't say that.

466
00:40:28.039 --> 00:40:31.265
Only Mommy says that word. She
coined it. it belongs to her.

467
00:40:31.273 --> 00:40:32.314
Why you up?

468
00:40:32.339 --> 00:40:34.964
'Cause I got some important shit
going on here. What do you think?

469
00:40:34.989 --> 00:40:38.126
No. I got something on my mind.
I got something on my mind.

470
00:40:38.151 --> 00:40:42.136
- Was it Juice Pops?
- Sure was.

471
00:40:43.873 --> 00:40:46.013
That's extortion.

472
00:40:47.029 --> 00:40:50.880
Great minds think alike. Juice
Pops. exactly was on...

473
00:40:52.404 --> 00:40:53.755
my mind.

474
00:40:54.576 --> 00:40:57.747
You done? Yeah? Now you are.

475
00:41:03.099 --> 00:41:06.184
- That face. goes there.
- Tell me a story.

476
00:41:06.451 --> 00:41:08.052
A story.

477
00:41:08.326 --> 00:41:10.857
Once upon a time. a little
girl went to bed. The end.

478
00:41:10.896 --> 00:41:12.226
That ain't the whole story.

479
00:41:12.251 --> 00:41:14.501
Come on. that's your
favorite story.

480
00:41:14.585 --> 00:41:16.053
I love you tons.

481
00:41:17.773 --> 00:41:20.295
I love you 3.000.

482
00:41:21.202 --> 00:41:22.202
Wow.

483
00:41:29.338 --> 00:41:32.361
3.000. That's crazy.

484
00:41:33.198 --> 00:41:35.731
Go to bed. Or I'll
sell all your toys.

485
00:41:36.065 --> 00:41:37.260
Night-night.

486
00:41:38.033 --> 00:41:41.705
Not that it's a competition.
but she loves me 3.000.

487
00:41:42.502 --> 00:41:46.400
You were somewhere in
the low 6 to 900 range.

488
00:41:52.037 --> 00:41:56.076
- What you reading?
- Just a book on composting.

489
00:41:56.101 --> 00:41:58.318
What's new with composting?

490
00:41:59.584 --> 00:42:01.217
- Just ....
- I figured it out...

491
00:42:02.225 --> 00:42:03.693
by the way.

492
00:42:04.903 --> 00:42:07.473
You know. just so we're talking
about the same thing...

493
00:42:07.919 --> 00:42:09.301
Time travel.

494
00:42:10.434 --> 00:42:11.434
What?

495
00:42:14.896 --> 00:42:15.896
Wow.

496
00:42:18.193 --> 00:42:19.193
That's...

497
00:42:19.966 --> 00:42:23.693
Amazing. and.... terrifying.

498
00:42:23.756 --> 00:42:24.935
That's right.

499
00:42:32.640 --> 00:42:36.836
- I got really lucky.
- Yeah. I know.

500
00:42:36.906 --> 00:42:40.031
- A lot of people didn't.
- No. I can't help everybody.

501
00:42:41.316 --> 00:42:44.269
- It sorta seems like you can.
- Not if I stop.

502
00:42:45.816 --> 00:42:49.011
I can put a pin in it
right now. and stop.

503
00:42:49.370 --> 00:42:50.636
Tony...

504
00:42:51.121 --> 00:42:56.253
trying to get you to stop has been one
of the few failures of my entire life.

505
00:43:00.123 --> 00:43:05.740
I sometimes feel I should put it in a locked
box and drop it at the bottom of a lake...

506
00:43:06.490 --> 00:43:08.333
...go to bed.

507
00:43:14.062 --> 00:43:16.570
But would you be able to rest?

508
00:43:21.069 --> 00:43:24.154
Okay. here we go. Time
travel test number one.

509
00:43:24.374 --> 00:43:29.069
Scott. fire up the. uhh...
The van thing.

510
00:43:30.977 --> 00:43:34.470
Breakers are set. Emergency
generators are on standby.

511
00:43:34.501 --> 00:43:39.345
Good. 'Cause if we blow the grid. I don't
wanna lose Tiny here in the 1950's.

512
00:43:39.439 --> 00:43:41.759
- Excuse me?
- He's kidding.

513
00:43:42.024 --> 00:43:43.843
You can't say things like that.

514
00:43:43.868 --> 00:43:46.969
Just... it was. just a bad joke.

515
00:43:48.321 --> 00:43:50.594
- You were kidding. right?
- I have no idea.

516
00:43:50.671 --> 00:43:54.811
We're talking about time travel here.
Either it's all a joke. or none of it is.

517
00:43:55.170 --> 00:43:57.982
We're good! Get your helmet on.

518
00:43:58.693 --> 00:44:01.419
Scott. I'm gonna send you
back a week. but you'll walk

519
00:44:01.444 --> 00:44:04.443
around for an hour. then bring
you back in 10 seconds.

520
00:44:04.623 --> 00:44:07.069
- Makes sense?
- Perfectly not confusing.

521
00:44:07.094 --> 00:44:09.695
Good luck. Scott. You got this.

522
00:44:10.670 --> 00:44:14.447
You're right. I do.
Captain America.

523
00:44:16.103 --> 00:44:21.946
On the count of three.
3.. 2.. 1..

524
00:44:25.701 --> 00:44:28.982
Guys? This doesn't feel right.

525
00:44:29.122 --> 00:44:30.990
- What's going on? Hold on.
- Who is that?

526
00:44:31.015 --> 00:44:33.022
- Is that Scott?
- Yes. it's Scott!

527
00:44:36.096 --> 00:44:37.807
Ooh! My back!

528
00:44:40.373 --> 00:44:42.815
- Can you bring him back?
- I'm working on it!

529
00:44:49.752 --> 00:44:50.752
A baby.

530
00:44:50.777 --> 00:44:52.362
- It's Scott.
- As a baby!

531
00:44:53.032 --> 00:44:54.088
Bring Scott back.

532
00:44:54.113 --> 00:44:56.408
When I say kill the
power. kill the power.

533
00:44:57.619 --> 00:44:59.689
And... kill it!

534
00:45:03.138 --> 00:45:05.528
Somebody peed my pants.

535
00:45:06.786 --> 00:45:09.793
I don't know if it was
"baby" me or "old" me.

536
00:45:13.155 --> 00:45:15.163
Or. just "me" me.

537
00:45:15.218 --> 00:45:17.046
Time travel!

538
00:45:20.570 --> 00:45:21.570
What?

539
00:45:22.913 --> 00:45:25.709
I see this as an absolute win.

540
00:46:10.909 --> 00:46:12.112
Why the long face?

541
00:46:12.175 --> 00:46:14.104
Let me guess. He
turned into a baby.

542
00:46:15.130 --> 00:46:17.317
Among other things. yeah.
What are you doing here?

543
00:46:17.380 --> 00:46:19.340
That's the EPR paradox.

544
00:46:19.536 --> 00:46:23.185
Instead of pushing Lang through time. you
might've wound up pushing time through Lang.

545
00:46:23.210 --> 00:46:26.161
It's tricky. Dangerous. Somebody
coulda cautioned you against it.

546
00:46:26.171 --> 00:46:28.592
- You did.
- Oh. did I?

547
00:46:29.315 --> 00:46:33.893
Thank God. I'm here.
Regardless. I fixed it.

548
00:46:33.918 --> 00:46:36.338
A fully functioning
time-space GPS.

549
00:46:38.359 --> 00:46:40.425
I just want peace.

550
00:46:40.968 --> 00:46:44.257
Turns out. resentment is
corrosive. and I hate it.

551
00:46:44.771 --> 00:46:46.091
Me. too.

552
00:46:47.356 --> 00:46:49.189
We got a shot at getting
these stones. but I

553
00:46:49.214 --> 00:46:50.965
gotta tell you my
priority is to bring back

554
00:46:50.995 --> 00:46:53.384
what we lost? I hope. yes.

555
00:46:53.409 --> 00:46:56.276
Keep what I found? I
have to. at all costs.

556
00:46:57.503 --> 00:47:01.346
And. maybe not die
trying will be nice.

557
00:47:03.737 --> 00:47:05.635
Sounds like a deal.

558
00:47:28.683 --> 00:47:32.729
- Tony. I don't know...
- Why? He made it for you.

559
00:47:33.378 --> 00:47:37.784
Plus. honestly I have to get it out the
garage before Morgan takes it sledding.

560
00:47:42.516 --> 00:47:43.891
Thank you. Tony.

561
00:47:44.633 --> 00:47:48.781
Will you keep that a little quietly?
Didn't bring one for the whole team.

562
00:47:49.904 --> 00:47:55.380
- We are getting. the whole team. yeah?
- We're working on that right now.

563
00:48:13.478 --> 00:48:18.986
- Hey. humie! Where's big green?
- Kitchen. I think.

564
00:48:20.284 --> 00:48:24.549
- That's awesome.
- Rodent. careful on re-entry.

565
00:48:24.565 --> 00:48:27.166
There's an idiot on
the landing zone.

566
00:48:27.687 --> 00:48:28.687
Oh. God!

567
00:48:29.585 --> 00:48:32.069
What's up. regular-sized man?

568
00:49:22.411 --> 00:49:26.848
Kind of a step down from a golden palace
for an Avenger highness or whatnot.

569
00:49:26.873 --> 00:49:29.364
Hey. have a little compassion. pal.
First. they've lost Asgard.

570
00:49:29.389 --> 00:49:32.280
then half the people. They're probably
just happy they have a home.

571
00:49:32.305 --> 00:49:34.422
You shouldn't have come!

572
00:49:35.914 --> 00:49:36.914
Valkyrie!

573
00:49:37.456 --> 00:49:39.791
Great to see you. Angry Girl.

574
00:49:40.088 --> 00:49:43.220
I think I liked you better
either of the other ways.

575
00:49:43.665 --> 00:49:45.844
- This is Rocket.
- How you doin'?

576
00:49:47.907 --> 00:49:50.032
- He won't see you.
- That bad. huh?

577
00:49:50.432 --> 00:49:52.721
We only see him once a month.
when he comes in for...

578
00:49:53.971 --> 00:49:55.361
...supplies.

579
00:49:55.915 --> 00:49:57.915
- It's that bad.
- Yeah.

580
00:50:10.612 --> 00:50:11.737
What the...

581
00:50:14.286 --> 00:50:17.348
Woo! Something died in here.

582
00:50:17.989 --> 00:50:20.207
Hello? Thor?

583
00:50:20.676 --> 00:50:22.808
Are you here about the cable?

584
00:50:23.051 --> 00:50:28.637
The Cinemax ran out two weeks ago.
and. sports were all kind of fuzzy...

585
00:50:38.350 --> 00:50:41.131
Boys! Oh. my God!

586
00:50:42.670 --> 00:50:44.967
My God! How have you been?

587
00:50:45.170 --> 00:50:47.170
Come here. you little rascal!

588
00:50:47.654 --> 00:50:49.193
No. I'm good! I'm good.

589
00:50:49.568 --> 00:50:51.326
That's not necessary!

590
00:50:51.370 --> 00:50:54.182
Hulk. you know my friends.
Miek. Korg. right?

591
00:50:54.214 --> 00:50:56.577
- Hey. boys!
- Hey. guys. Long time no see.

592
00:50:56.602 --> 00:50:59.471
Beer's on the bucket. Feel
free to log on to the wi-fi.

593
00:50:59.496 --> 00:51:01.205
No password. obviously.

594
00:51:02.148 --> 00:51:06.210
Thor. he's back. That kid on the TV
who's called me a dickhead again.

595
00:51:07.046 --> 00:51:10.273
- Noobmaster.
- Yeah. Noobmaster69.

596
00:51:12.906 --> 00:51:15.906
Noobmaster. Hey. it's Thor again.
You know. the God of Thunder?

597
00:51:15.937 --> 00:51:18.976
Listen. buddy. If you don't log off
this game immediately I'm gonna fly

598
00:51:19.001 --> 00:51:21.820
home to your house. come down to
that basement you're hiding in.

599
00:51:21.845 --> 00:51:24.281
rip off your arms then
shove them up your butt!

600
00:51:24.697 --> 00:51:27.791
Oh. that's right. Yes. go cry to
your father. you little weasel!

601
00:51:28.095 --> 00:51:29.244
Thank you. Thor.

602
00:51:29.269 --> 00:51:30.855
Let me know if he
bothers you again. okay?

603
00:51:30.880 --> 00:51:32.376
Thank you very much. I will.

604
00:51:32.930 --> 00:51:34.602
So you guys want a drink?
What are you drinking?

605
00:51:34.627 --> 00:51:37.095
We have beer. tequila.
all sorts of things.

606
00:51:40.134 --> 00:51:42.689
Buddy. you all right?

607
00:51:42.736 --> 00:51:45.548
Yes. I'm fine! Why.
don't I look all right?

608
00:51:45.673 --> 00:51:47.720
You look like melted ice cream.

609
00:51:49.143 --> 00:51:51.588
So. what's up?

610
00:51:51.620 --> 00:51:56.064
We need your help. There might be
a chance we could fix everything.

611
00:51:56.120 --> 00:51:59.869
What. like the cable? 'Cause that's
been driving me bananas for weeks.

612
00:51:59.916 --> 00:52:01.307
Like Thanos.

613
00:52:20.017 --> 00:52:23.073
Don't say that name.

614
00:52:23.618 --> 00:52:26.681
Um. yeah. We don't actually
say that name in here.

615
00:52:31.498 --> 00:52:33.521
Please take your hand off me.

616
00:52:36.467 --> 00:52:37.467
Now. I know that...

617
00:52:38.981 --> 00:52:41.824
guy might scare you.

618
00:52:42.083 --> 00:52:46.364
Why would I be? Why would. why
would I be scared of that guy?

619
00:52:46.951 --> 00:52:49.279
I'm the one who killed
that guy. remember?

620
00:52:50.020 --> 00:52:52.458
Anyone else here
killed that guy?

621
00:52:55.399 --> 00:52:58.492
Nope. Didn't think so.

622
00:52:59.102 --> 00:53:03.227
Korg. why don't you. tell everybody
who chopped Thanos' big head off.

623
00:53:03.252 --> 00:53:05.016
Umm... Stormbreaker?

624
00:53:05.041 --> 00:53:07.563
Now. who's swinging
Stormbreaker?

625
00:53:10.735 --> 00:53:14.307
I get it. You're in a rough spot. okay?
I've been there myself.

626
00:53:14.315 --> 00:53:16.557
You wanna know who
helped me out of it?

627
00:53:16.581 --> 00:53:19.533
I don't know. Is it... Natasha?

628
00:53:19.557 --> 00:53:20.721
It was you.

629
00:53:21.635 --> 00:53:23.283
You helped me.

630
00:53:24.939 --> 00:53:29.603
Why don't you ask the.
Asgardians down there.

631
00:53:29.627 --> 00:53:32.158
how much my help was worth.

632
00:53:37.038 --> 00:53:39.003
The ones that are left. anyway.

633
00:53:39.252 --> 00:53:41.034
I think we can bring them back.

634
00:53:41.526 --> 00:53:44.752
Stop. Just. stop...

635
00:53:45.677 --> 00:53:50.700
I know you think I'm down here wallowing in
my own self-pity. waiting to be rescued and

636
00:53:50.725 --> 00:53:53.539
and saved. But I'm fine. okay?
We're fine. aren't we?

637
00:53:53.564 --> 00:53:54.812
Nah. all good here. mate!

638
00:53:54.837 --> 00:53:56.695
So. whatever it is that
you're offering. we're

639
00:53:56.720 --> 00:53:59.070
not into it. don't care.
couldn't care less.

640
00:53:59.102 --> 00:54:00.226
Goodbye.

641
00:54:03.608 --> 00:54:04.882
We need you. pal.

642
00:54:14.664 --> 00:54:16.649
There's beer on the ship.

643
00:54:20.877 --> 00:54:22.010
What kind?

644
00:54:34.685 --> 00:54:37.035
It's him! He's after Akihiko!

645
00:55:07.887 --> 00:55:09.668
We never did anything to you!

646
00:55:22.096 --> 00:55:24.543
You're done hurting people.

647
00:55:30.687 --> 00:55:31.866
You're crazy!

648
00:55:59.090 --> 00:56:02.847
Wait! Help me!

649
00:56:08.527 --> 00:56:09.996
What I want...

650
00:56:10.717 --> 00:56:12.161
You can't give me.

651
00:56:35.673 --> 00:56:37.352
You shouldn't be here.

652
00:56:39.352 --> 00:56:40.907
Neither should you.

653
00:56:46.955 --> 00:56:48.603
I've got a job to do.

654
00:56:50.204 --> 00:56:52.282
Is that what you're
calling this?

655
00:56:52.892 --> 00:56:56.094
Killing all these people isn't
gonna bring your family back.

656
00:57:01.209 --> 00:57:02.802
We found something.

657
00:57:04.029 --> 00:57:06.130
A chance. maybe...

658
00:57:09.538 --> 00:57:10.623
Don't.

659
00:57:11.788 --> 00:57:13.155
Don't what?

660
00:57:15.858 --> 00:57:17.655
Don't give me hope.

661
00:57:20.972 --> 00:57:23.636
I'm sorry I couldn't
give it to you sooner.

662
00:57:45.077 --> 00:57:48.702
Drifting left. On the
side there. Lebowski.

663
00:57:51.828 --> 00:57:54.017
- Ratchet. how's it going?
- It's Rocket.

664
00:57:54.042 --> 00:57:57.135
Take it easy. You're only
a genius on Earth. pal.

665
00:57:57.190 --> 00:57:58.190
Yup.

666
00:58:01.691 --> 00:58:04.206
Time travel suit? Not bad.

667
00:58:04.634 --> 00:58:06.275
Hey. hey. hey. Easy. easy!

668
00:58:06.306 --> 00:58:09.063
- I'm being very careful.
- No. you're being very Hulky.

669
00:58:09.072 --> 00:58:11.647
- I'm being careful.
- These are Pym particles. all right?

670
00:58:11.672 --> 00:58:14.423
And ever since Hank Pym got snapped
out of existence. this is it.

671
00:58:14.448 --> 00:58:16.501
This is what we have. We're
not making any more.

672
00:58:16.526 --> 00:58:18.271
- Scott. calm down.
- Sorry.

673
00:58:18.310 --> 00:58:20.675
We've got enough for
one round trip. each.

674
00:58:20.700 --> 00:58:24.653
That's it. No do-overs.
Plus. two test runs.

675
00:58:29.206 --> 00:58:30.487
One test run.

676
00:58:31.284 --> 00:58:33.081
All right. I'm not
ready for this.

677
00:58:33.106 --> 00:58:34.190
I'm game.

678
00:58:36.745 --> 00:58:37.831
I'll do it.

679
00:58:38.870 --> 00:58:41.151
Clint. now you're gonna feel
a little discombobulated

680
00:58:41.176 --> 00:58:42.909
from the chronoshift.
Don't worry about it.

681
00:58:42.917 --> 00:58:44.243
Wait a second. let me
ask you something.

682
00:58:44.268 --> 00:58:47.088
If we can do this. you know. go
back in time. why don't we just

683
00:58:47.113 --> 00:58:50.299
find baby Thanos. you know?
And...

684
00:58:53.605 --> 00:58:55.846
- First of all. that's horrible.
- It's Thanos.

685
00:58:55.871 --> 00:59:00.410
And secondly. time doesn't work that way.
Changing the past doesn't change the future.

686
00:59:00.435 --> 00:59:03.302
Look. we go back. we get the
stones before Thanos gets them...

687
00:59:03.327 --> 00:59:06.225
Thanos doesn't have the stones.
Problem solved.

688
00:59:06.250 --> 00:59:08.107
- Bingo.
- That's not how it works.

689
00:59:08.132 --> 00:59:10.544
- Well. that's what I heard.
- What? By who? Who told you that?

690
00:59:10.577 --> 00:59:13.389
Star Trek. Terminator.
TimeCop. Time After Time.

691
00:59:13.414 --> 00:59:14.739
- Quantum Leap.
- A Wrinkle in Time.

692
00:59:14.764 --> 00:59:17.262
- Somewhere in Time.
- Hot Tub Time Machine.

693
00:59:17.287 --> 00:59:21.544
Bill and Ted's Excellent Adventure. Basically.
any movie that deals with time travel.

694
00:59:21.569 --> 00:59:23.413
Die Hard? No. it's not...

695
00:59:23.437 --> 00:59:24.476
This is known.

696
00:59:24.501 --> 00:59:26.843
I don't know why everyone believes
that. but that isn't true.

697
00:59:26.897 --> 00:59:31.186
Think about it: If you travel to the
past. that past becomes your future.

698
00:59:31.335 --> 00:59:34.556
And your former present
becomes the past.

699
00:59:34.642 --> 00:59:37.462
Which can't now be changed
by your new future...

700
00:59:37.506 --> 00:59:38.587
Exactly.

701
00:59:38.906 --> 00:59:41.562
So Back to the Future's
a bunch of bullshit?

702
00:59:46.384 --> 00:59:52.477
All right. Clint. We're going in 3..
2.. 1...

703
01:01:04.895 --> 01:01:06.043
Cooper?

704
01:01:06.247 --> 01:01:09.083
- Where are my headphones?
- Lila?

705
01:01:14.387 --> 01:01:15.997
Lila! No!

706
01:01:21.232 --> 01:01:22.232
Dad?

707
01:01:26.138 --> 01:01:27.216
Dad?

708
01:01:37.720 --> 01:01:40.243
Hey. hey. Look at me. You okay?

709
01:01:41.095 --> 01:01:42.095
Yeah.

710
01:01:44.992 --> 01:01:46.290
It worked.

711
01:01:47.942 --> 01:01:49.106
It worked.

712
01:01:52.489 --> 01:01:54.410
Okay. so the "how" works.

713
01:01:54.919 --> 01:01:58.208
Now we gotta figure out the
"when." and the "where."

714
01:01:59.134 --> 01:02:00.868
Almost everyone in this
room has had an encounter

715
01:02:00.893 --> 01:02:02.719
with at least one of the
six Infinity Stones.

716
01:02:02.759 --> 01:02:04.523
Well. I'd subtitute the
word 'encounter' for 'damn

717
01:02:04.548 --> 01:02:07.009
near been killed by one of
the six Infinity Stones.'

718
01:02:07.204 --> 01:02:10.625
I haven't. I don't even know what
the hell you're all talking about.

719
01:02:10.750 --> 01:02:15.742
Regardless. we only have enough Pym
Particles for one round trip each.

720
01:02:15.789 --> 01:02:19.148
and these stones have been in a lot of
different places throughout history.

721
01:02:19.173 --> 01:02:23.343
Our history. So. not a lot of
convenient spots to just drop in.

722
01:02:23.531 --> 01:02:27.093
- Which means we have to pick our targets.
- Correct.

723
01:02:27.187 --> 01:02:30.358
So. Let's start
 with the Aether.

724
01:02:30.522 --> 01:02:32.459
Thor. what do you know?

725
01:02:37.436 --> 01:02:38.654
Is he asleep?

726
01:02:44.171 --> 01:02:46.506
Where to start? Umm...

727
01:02:47.648 --> 01:02:50.483
The Aether. first.
is not a stone.

728
01:02:50.663 --> 01:02:54.054
Someone's called it a stone before.
Ahem...

729
01:02:54.116 --> 01:02:57.819
It's more of a... an angry
sludge. sort of thing. So...

730
01:02:57.844 --> 01:03:00.984
Someone's gonna need to amend
that. and stop saying that.

731
01:03:01.191 --> 01:03:03.124
Here's an interesting
story. though.

732
01:03:03.205 --> 01:03:05.653
About the Aether. My
grandafther. many years

733
01:03:05.678 --> 01:03:09.681
ago. had to hide the stone
from the Dark Elves.

734
01:03:11.707 --> 01:03:13.488
Scary beings. So Jane...

735
01:03:14.832 --> 01:03:20.628
Oh. there she is. That's Jane...
She's... an old flame of mine.

736
01:03:21.228 --> 01:03:24.634
She... she stuck her hand
inside a rock this one time...

737
01:03:24.670 --> 01:03:27.993
and then the Aether stuck
itself inside her.

738
01:03:28.014 --> 01:03:31.217
And. she became very. very sick.
So I had to take her to

739
01:03:31.242 --> 01:03:34.976
Asgard. which is where I'm from.
And we had to try and fix her.

740
01:03:35.031 --> 01:03:40.648
We were dating at the time. you see. I
got to introduce her to my Mother...

741
01:03:42.064 --> 01:03:44.299
who's dead. and umm....

742
01:03:45.311 --> 01:03:49.108
Oh. you know. Jane and I aren't
even dating anymore. so...

743
01:03:49.443 --> 01:03:51.982
These things happen though. you know.
Nothing lasts forever.

744
01:03:52.007 --> 01:03:53.239
- The only thing that...
- Why don't you come sit down.

745
01:03:53.264 --> 01:03:57.663
I'm not done yet. The only thing that
is permanent in life. is impermanence.

746
01:03:58.421 --> 01:03:59.529
Awesome.

747
01:03:59.554 --> 01:04:00.725
Eggs? Breakfast?

748
01:04:00.750 --> 01:04:02.688
No. I'd like a Bloody Mary.

749
01:04:02.747 --> 01:04:05.600
Quill said he stole the
Power Stone from Morag.

750
01:04:05.843 --> 01:04:09.155
- Is that a person?
- Morag's a planet.

751
01:04:09.434 --> 01:04:11.129
Quill was a person.

752
01:04:11.730 --> 01:04:14.300
Like a planet? Like
in outer space?

753
01:04:14.425 --> 01:04:18.230
Oh. look. It's like a little
puppy. all happy and everything.

754
01:04:18.362 --> 01:04:21.885
Do you wanna go to space? You
wanna go to space. puppy?

755
01:04:21.950 --> 01:04:24.133
I'll take you to space.

756
01:04:24.423 --> 01:04:28.055
- Thanos found the Soul Stone on Vormir.
- What is Vormir?

757
01:04:28.626 --> 01:04:33.118
A dominion of death. at the very
center of Celestial existence.

758
01:04:34.511 --> 01:04:38.300
It's where... Thanos
murdered my sister.

759
01:04:44.712 --> 01:04:45.712
Noted.

760
01:04:47.571 --> 01:04:49.672
- That Time Stone guy...
- Doctor Strange.

761
01:04:49.712 --> 01:04:51.258
Yeah. what kind
of doctor was he?

762
01:04:51.266 --> 01:04:54.922
- Neurostuff meets rabbit from a hat.
- Nice place in the village. though.

763
01:04:54.954 --> 01:04:57.405
- Yeah. Sullivan Street.
- Hmm... Bleecker.

764
01:04:57.430 --> 01:04:59.039
Wait. he lived in New York?

765
01:04:59.304 --> 01:05:02.280
- No. He lived in Toronto.
- Yeah. not Bleecker. It's Sullivan.

766
01:05:02.652 --> 01:05:07.534
Guys. if you pick the right year.
there are three stones in New York.

767
01:05:09.816 --> 01:05:11.253
Shut the front door!

768
01:05:14.199 --> 01:05:16.737
All right. We have a plan.

769
01:05:16.815 --> 01:05:21.447
Six stones. three
teams. one shot.

770
01:05:30.773 --> 01:05:32.875
Five years ago. we lost.

771
01:05:33.883 --> 01:05:35.062
All of us.

772
01:05:37.149 --> 01:05:38.196
We lost friends...

773
01:05:39.593 --> 01:05:40.687
We lost family...

774
01:05:43.067 --> 01:05:44.879
We lost a part of ourselves.

775
01:05:46.106 --> 01:05:48.567
Today. we have a chance
to take it all back.

776
01:05:49.784 --> 01:05:52.963
You know your teams. you
know your missions.

777
01:05:53.377 --> 01:05:56.205
Get the stones. get them back.

778
01:05:56.260 --> 01:06:00.620
One round trip each. No mistakes.
No do-overs.

779
01:06:01.042 --> 01:06:03.258
Most of us are going
somewhere we know.

780
01:06:03.312 --> 01:06:05.999
But it doesn't mean we
should know what to expect.

781
01:06:06.218 --> 01:06:09.421
Be careful. Look out
for each other.

782
01:06:10.500 --> 01:06:14.648
This is the fight of our lives.
And we're gonna win.

783
01:06:16.920 --> 01:06:18.375
Whatever it takes.

784
01:06:21.070 --> 01:06:22.367
Good luck.

785
01:06:23.046 --> 01:06:24.836
- He's pretty good at that.
- Right?

786
01:06:24.914 --> 01:06:27.851
All right. You heard the man.
Stroke those keys. jelly green.

787
01:06:28.561 --> 01:06:30.670
Tractors engaged.

788
01:06:31.047 --> 01:06:33.084
You promise to bring that
back in one piece. right?

789
01:06:33.109 --> 01:06:35.100
Yeah. yeah. yeah.
yeah. Okay.

790
01:06:35.125 --> 01:06:38.883
- I'll do my best.
- As promises go. that was pretty lame.

791
01:06:41.440 --> 01:06:42.922
See you in a minute.

792
01:07:37.039 --> 01:07:40.453
All right. we all have our assignments.
Two stones uptown. one stone. down.

793
01:07:40.875 --> 01:07:43.257
Stay low. Keep an
eye on the clock.

794
01:07:58.089 --> 01:08:00.424
Feel free to smash if
things don't go your way.

795
01:08:01.214 --> 01:08:03.393
I think it's gratuitous.
but whatever.

796
01:08:30.825 --> 01:08:34.278
I'd be careful going that way.
We just had the floors waxed.

797
01:08:38.793 --> 01:08:41.433
Ma'am. I'm looking
for Doctor Strange.

798
01:08:42.722 --> 01:08:45.644
You're about... five
years too early.

799
01:08:46.034 --> 01:08:50.370
Stephen Strange is currently performing
surgery about twenty blocks that way.

800
01:08:51.671 --> 01:08:53.440
What do you want from him?

801
01:08:53.811 --> 01:08:55.342
That. actually.

802
01:08:55.631 --> 01:08:56.631
Ah.

803
01:08:57.968 --> 01:09:01.139
- I'm afraid not.
- Sorry. but I wasn't asking.

804
01:09:01.663 --> 01:09:03.591
- You don't wanna do this.
- You're right. I don't.

805
01:09:03.616 --> 01:09:06.850
But I need that stone. and
I don't have time to...

806
01:09:14.872 --> 01:09:16.848
Let's start over. shall we?

807
01:09:36.148 --> 01:09:37.304
That's Jane.

808
01:09:38.945 --> 01:09:40.023
All right.

809
01:09:41.623 --> 01:09:43.201
Here's the deal. Tubby:

810
01:09:43.210 --> 01:09:45.299
You're gonna charm her and I'm
gonna poke her with this thing

811
01:09:45.324 --> 01:09:48.553
and extract the Reality Stone
and get gone. lickety-split.

812
01:09:49.601 --> 01:09:52.905
I'll be right back. okay? There's a
wine cellar. that's just down there.

813
01:09:52.930 --> 01:09:55.726
My father used to fish
with a barrel of ale.

814
01:09:55.781 --> 01:09:59.984
- I'll see if the cellar has a couple of...
- Hey! Aren't you drunk enough already?

815
01:10:18.787 --> 01:10:20.677
Who's the fancy broad?

816
01:10:21.538 --> 01:10:25.202
It's my Mother.
She dies today.

817
01:10:26.287 --> 01:10:28.154
Oh. That's today?

818
01:10:34.290 --> 01:10:37.352
I can't do this.
I can't do this.

819
01:10:37.377 --> 01:10:40.711
I shouldn't be here. I shouldn't have come.
This was a bad idea.

820
01:10:40.821 --> 01:10:43.055
- Come here.
- No. no. no. I think I'm having...

821
01:10:43.094 --> 01:10:46.539
- I'm having a panic attack.
- Come here. Right here.

822
01:10:47.071 --> 01:10:50.953
You think you're the only one who lost
people? What do you think we're doing here?

823
01:10:50.978 --> 01:10:53.148
I lost the only
family I ever had.

824
01:10:53.173 --> 01:10:57.352
Quill. Groot. Drax. the chick
with the antenna. all gone.

825
01:10:57.954 --> 01:11:02.399
Now. I get you miss your Mom.
But she's gone. Really gone.

826
01:11:02.712 --> 01:11:05.540
And there are plenty of people
who are only kinda gone.

827
01:11:05.579 --> 01:11:07.392
But you can help them.

828
01:11:07.820 --> 01:11:11.199
So is it too much to ask that you
brush the crumbs outta your beard.

829
01:11:11.224 --> 01:11:15.177
make schmoopy talk to Pretty
Pants. and when she's not looking.

830
01:11:15.404 --> 01:11:19.310
suck out the Infinity Stone and
help me get my family back?

831
01:11:20.245 --> 01:11:21.245
Okay.

832
01:11:21.713 --> 01:11:24.432
- Are you crying?
- No...

833
01:11:26.577 --> 01:11:27.577
Yes!

834
01:11:27.717 --> 01:11:30.264
Get it together!
You can do this.

835
01:11:30.858 --> 01:11:32.514
You can do this.

836
01:11:35.585 --> 01:11:36.764
All right?

837
01:11:37.093 --> 01:11:39.280
- Yes. I can.
- Good.

838
01:11:41.085 --> 01:11:43.506
I can do this.

839
01:11:44.506 --> 01:11:45.748
I can't do this.

840
01:11:45.928 --> 01:11:49.513
Alright. Heartbreaker. She's alone.
This is our shot.

841
01:11:49.568 --> 01:11:50.568
Thor?

842
01:11:51.201 --> 01:11:52.201
Thor!

843
01:12:02.503 --> 01:12:04.159
Alright. Bring it down low.

844
01:12:04.184 --> 01:12:06.727
Right on that line. That's it.
Down. down.

845
01:12:11.570 --> 01:12:12.573
Hey. can we hurry it up?

846
01:12:12.598 --> 01:12:14.804
Guys. chop-chop. Come on.
We're on the clock.

847
01:12:14.949 --> 01:12:17.811
All that. is really helpful.

848
01:12:19.075 --> 01:12:20.769
- Take care. okay?
- Yeah.

849
01:12:20.889 --> 01:12:23.387
Take that stone and come back.
No messing around.

850
01:12:23.636 --> 01:12:25.448
- Hey.
- You got this.

851
01:12:25.545 --> 01:12:26.794
- Let's get it done.
- Yes. sir.

852
01:12:26.854 --> 01:12:28.466
See you back.

853
01:12:28.981 --> 01:12:30.904
You guys watch each other's six.

854
01:12:30.912 --> 01:12:31.912
Yeah.

855
01:12:40.826 --> 01:12:43.240
The coordinates for
Vormir are laid in.

856
01:12:44.027 --> 01:12:46.534
All they have to do
is not fall out.

857
01:12:51.938 --> 01:12:54.570
We're a long way from Budapest.

858
01:12:58.857 --> 01:13:00.239
Okay. so. uhh...

859
01:13:01.925 --> 01:13:04.869
We just wait around for this
Quill guy to show up and

860
01:13:04.894 --> 01:13:07.566
then he leads us to the
Power Stone. is that it?

861
01:13:08.027 --> 01:13:09.652
Let's take cover.

862
01:13:10.605 --> 01:13:13.636
We're not the only ones in
2014 looking for the stones.

863
01:13:13.761 --> 01:13:15.175
Wait a minute. what are
you talking about right

864
01:13:15.200 --> 01:13:17.143
now? Who else is looking
for these stones?

865
01:13:20.210 --> 01:13:22.742
My father. my sister...

866
01:13:23.722 --> 01:13:26.206
- and me.
- And you?

867
01:13:27.884 --> 01:13:29.844
Where are you right now?

868
01:13:58.404 --> 01:14:01.670
- You're welcome.
- I didn't ask for your help.

869
01:14:02.396 --> 01:14:05.005
And yet. you always need it.

870
01:14:08.108 --> 01:14:09.225
Get up.

871
01:14:09.311 --> 01:14:11.670
- Father wants us back on the ship.
- Why?

872
01:14:11.725 --> 01:14:14.209
He's found an Infinity Stone.

873
01:14:17.913 --> 01:14:21.647
- Where?
- On a planet called Morag.

874
01:14:23.010 --> 01:14:25.299
Father's plan is
finally in motion.

875
01:14:25.324 --> 01:14:28.683
- One stone isn't six. Nebula.
- It's a start.

876
01:14:28.844 --> 01:14:31.351
If he gets all of them...

877
01:14:43.292 --> 01:14:47.011
Ronan's located the Power Stone.
I'm dispatching you to his ship.

878
01:14:47.036 --> 01:14:50.394
- He won't like that.
- His alternative is death. then.

879
01:14:52.099 --> 01:14:56.989
Ronan's obsession
clouds his judgement.

880
01:15:01.262 --> 01:15:03.333
We will not fail you. Father.

881
01:15:04.435 --> 01:15:06.263
No. you won't.

882
01:15:08.796 --> 01:15:10.124
I swear...

883
01:15:11.618 --> 01:15:13.796
I will make you proud.

884
01:15:21.910 --> 01:15:25.095
We just. wait around for
this Quill guy to show up.

885
01:15:25.120 --> 01:15:27.714
and then he leads us to the
Power Stone. is that it?

886
01:15:28.098 --> 01:15:29.574
Let's take cover.

887
01:15:30.472 --> 01:15:34.011
We're not the only ones in
2014 looking for the stones.

888
01:15:35.886 --> 01:15:38.081
- Who was that?
- I don't know...

889
01:15:38.143 --> 01:15:41.221
My head is splitting...
I don't know...

890
01:15:42.408 --> 01:15:45.741
Her synaptic drive was
probably damaged in battle.

891
01:15:55.470 --> 01:15:57.368
Bring her to my ship.

892
01:16:05.348 --> 01:16:07.903
Got to hustle. Cap. Things look like
they're just about wrapped up here.

893
01:16:07.928 --> 01:16:10.513
Got it. I'm approaching
the elevator now.

894
01:16:16.432 --> 01:16:18.432
If it's all the same to you...

895
01:16:20.572 --> 01:16:22.239
I'll have that drink now.

896
01:16:22.510 --> 01:16:26.931
All right. Good one. No standing around.
I'm closing up this door for later.

897
01:16:26.970 --> 01:16:28.915
By the way. feel
free to clean up.

898
01:16:28.962 --> 01:16:31.571
Ugh. Mr. Rogers. I almost
forgot that that suit

899
01:16:31.617 --> 01:16:35.055
- did nothing for your ass.
- No one asked you to look.

900
01:16:35.114 --> 01:16:37.121
I think you look great. Cap.

901
01:16:37.146 --> 01:16:40.837
As far as I'm concerned.
that's America's ass.

902
01:16:40.950 --> 01:16:44.056
- Uhh. magic wand?
- STRIKE team's coming to secure it.

903
01:16:54.199 --> 01:16:56.112
We can take that
off your hands.

904
01:16:56.214 --> 01:16:57.440
By all means.

905
01:16:59.262 --> 01:17:02.855
- Careful with that thing!
- Unless you want your mind erased.

906
01:17:02.880 --> 01:17:05.051
- Not in a fun way.
- We promise to be careful.

907
01:17:05.086 --> 01:17:07.906
- Who are these guys?
- They are SHIELD...

908
01:17:07.945 --> 01:17:10.804
Well. actually Hydra. But.
we didn't know that yet.

909
01:17:10.854 --> 01:17:14.838
Seriously. you didn't? I mean...
they look like bad guys.

910
01:17:14.885 --> 01:17:16.738
You're small. but
you're talking loud.

911
01:17:16.763 --> 01:17:18.376
On my way down to
coordinate search and rescue.

912
01:17:18.401 --> 01:17:20.527
On my way down to
coordinate search and rescue!

913
01:17:20.552 --> 01:17:23.322
I mean. honestly! How do
you think you'll be...

914
01:17:23.347 --> 01:17:24.567
Shut up.

915
01:17:25.997 --> 01:17:28.903
All right. you're up. little buddy.
There's our stone.

916
01:17:29.075 --> 01:17:31.567
Alright. Flick me.

917
01:17:46.704 --> 01:17:48.302
- Whoa! Whoa. whoa.
- Hey! Buddy.

918
01:17:48.337 --> 01:17:50.734
What do you think? Maximum
occupancy has been reached.

919
01:17:50.759 --> 01:17:53.594
- Take the stairs!
- Yeah. Stop. Stop!

920
01:17:56.387 --> 01:17:59.496
Take the stairs.
Take the stairs!

921
01:18:02.832 --> 01:18:07.597
All right. Cap. I got our scepter in the
elevator just passing the 80th floor.

922
01:18:08.199 --> 01:18:09.215
On it.

923
01:18:09.902 --> 01:18:12.386
- Head to the lobby.
- Alright. I'll see you there.

924
01:18:12.411 --> 01:18:15.386
Evidence secure. We're
en route to Dr. List.

925
01:18:15.949 --> 01:18:19.316
No. No hitches at all. Mr.
Secretary.

926
01:18:24.480 --> 01:18:27.457
Captain. I thought you were
coordinating search and rescue?

927
01:18:27.543 --> 01:18:29.191
Change of plans.

928
01:18:32.705 --> 01:18:33.792
Hey. Cap.

929
01:18:35.140 --> 01:18:36.378
Rumlow.

930
01:18:42.913 --> 01:18:46.944
I just got a call from the Secretary. I'm
gonna be running point on the scepter.

931
01:18:49.115 --> 01:18:51.864
Sir? I don't understand.

932
01:18:53.811 --> 01:18:55.928
We got word there may be
an attempt to steal it.

933
01:18:55.953 --> 01:18:57.202
Sorry. Cap.

934
01:18:57.631 --> 01:18:59.519
I can't give you the scepter.

935
01:18:59.653 --> 01:19:03.988
- I'm gonna have to call the Director.
- That's okay. Trust me.

936
01:19:07.503 --> 01:19:09.049
Hail Hydra.

937
01:19:23.031 --> 01:19:25.125
So many stairs!

938
01:19:36.623 --> 01:19:39.404
Thumbelina. do you copy?
I've got eyes on the prize.

939
01:19:39.428 --> 01:19:41.920
- It is go-time.
- Bombs away.

940
01:19:49.246 --> 01:19:51.363
Is. is that Axe body spray?

941
01:19:51.388 --> 01:19:54.161
Yeah. I had a can just
for emergencies. Relax.

942
01:19:54.231 --> 01:19:58.301
- Can we focus. please?
- I'm going inside you. Now.

943
01:20:03.651 --> 01:20:05.396
May I ask you
where you're going?

944
01:20:05.421 --> 01:20:07.926
To lunch and then Asgard.
I'm sorry. you are?

945
01:20:07.951 --> 01:20:11.584
Alexander Pierce. He's the man. one
of the folks behind Nick Fury.

946
01:20:11.609 --> 01:20:13.075
My friends call me Mr. Secretary.

947
01:20:13.109 --> 01:20:15.577
I'm gonna have to ask you to
turn that prisoner over to me.

948
01:20:15.648 --> 01:20:18.702
- Loki will be answering to Odin himself.
- Oh. he's gonna answer to us.

949
01:20:18.727 --> 01:20:21.452
Odin can have what's left. And
I'm gonna need that case.

950
01:20:21.609 --> 01:20:23.609
That's been SHIELD property
for over 70 years.

951
01:20:23.634 --> 01:20:24.851
Hand over the case. Stark.

952
01:20:24.876 --> 01:20:27.517
All right. move it. Stuart Little. Things
are getting dicey up here. Let's go.

953
01:20:27.542 --> 01:20:29.709
I'm not gonna argue who's got the
higher authority here. all right?

954
01:20:29.734 --> 01:20:31.125
You promise me you won't die?

955
01:20:31.150 --> 01:20:34.131
You're only giving me a
mild cardiac dysrythmia.

956
01:20:34.186 --> 01:20:35.889
That doesn't sound mild.

957
01:20:35.914 --> 01:20:36.533
I need the case.

958
01:20:36.558 --> 01:20:38.391
I know you got a lotta pull.
I'm just saying...

959
01:20:38.416 --> 01:20:40.205
Okay. Then give me the case.

960
01:20:42.127 --> 01:20:43.127
Do it. Lang!

961
01:20:43.150 --> 01:20:45.877
- Get your hands off!
- Window's closing. Pull my pin!

962
01:20:46.040 --> 01:20:47.158
Here goes!

963
01:20:50.416 --> 01:20:52.291
- Stark?
- Stark!

964
01:20:52.330 --> 01:20:54.337
Look. he's convulsing.
Give him air!

965
01:20:54.362 --> 01:20:56.369
- Medic!
- Medic!

966
01:20:56.627 --> 01:20:58.611
You got some help!

967
01:20:59.854 --> 01:21:02.439
Stark. you--- your
chest machine?

968
01:21:04.220 --> 01:21:05.470
Breathe! Breathe!

969
01:21:10.754 --> 01:21:13.699
Good job. Meet me in the alley.
I'm gonna grab a quick slice.

970
01:21:19.136 --> 01:21:21.230
No stairs!

971
01:21:28.782 --> 01:21:30.291
You'll be fine. Stark.
Stay with us!

972
01:21:30.322 --> 01:21:33.353
I'll try something. okay? I have
no idea if it's gonna work.

973
01:21:34.915 --> 01:21:35.587
Yes!

974
01:21:35.612 --> 01:21:37.869
That worked a treat.
That was so crazy!

975
01:21:37.885 --> 01:21:39.900
I had no idea if
that was gonna work.

976
01:21:39.925 --> 01:21:41.766
- The case...
- The case. It's. uhh...

977
01:21:41.807 --> 01:21:44.275
Where's the case? Where's Loki?

978
01:21:44.548 --> 01:21:45.548
Loki!

979
01:21:45.580 --> 01:21:48.689
- That wasn't supposed to happen. was it?
- Oh. we blew it.

980
01:21:48.736 --> 01:21:50.142
Loki!?

981
01:21:52.220 --> 01:21:53.915
Tony. what's going on?

982
01:21:54.400 --> 01:21:56.548
Tell me you found that cube.

983
01:21:58.447 --> 01:22:00.509
Oh. you gotta be shitting me.

984
01:22:04.353 --> 01:22:06.752
I have eyes on Loki. 14th floor.

985
01:22:06.862 --> 01:22:08.174
I'm not Loki.

986
01:22:11.543 --> 01:22:13.527
And I don't wanna hurt you.

987
01:22:22.355 --> 01:22:23.636
I can do this all day.

988
01:22:23.661 --> 01:22:26.043
Yeah. I know. I know.

989
01:22:58.548 --> 01:23:00.407
Where did you get this?

990
01:23:10.934 --> 01:23:14.500
Bucky... is... alive!

991
01:23:17.343 --> 01:23:18.343
What?

992
01:23:33.339 --> 01:23:35.432
That is America's ass.

993
01:23:39.456 --> 01:23:42.362
- Please. please!
- I'm sorry. I can't help you. Bruce.

994
01:23:43.261 --> 01:23:46.885
If I give up the Time Stone to help
your reality. I'm dooming my own.

995
01:23:46.933 --> 01:23:51.784
With all due respect. I'm not sure
the science really supports that.

996
01:23:57.405 --> 01:24:01.545
The Infinity Stones create what you
experience as the flow of time.

997
01:24:01.784 --> 01:24:05.503
Remove one of the stones.
and that flow splits.

998
01:24:05.761 --> 01:24:10.823
Now this may benefit your reality.
But my new one. not so much.

999
01:24:10.863 --> 01:24:16.105
In this new branched reality. without our
chief weapon against the forces of darkness.

1000
01:24:16.328 --> 01:24:20.203
our world will be overrun.
Millions will suffer.

1001
01:24:20.320 --> 01:24:24.413
So. tell me. doctor. can your
science prevent all that?

1002
01:24:24.515 --> 01:24:27.811
No. But we can erase it.

1003
01:24:27.835 --> 01:24:31.741
Because once we're done with the stones. we
can return each one into its own timeline

1004
01:24:31.766 --> 01:24:36.124
at the moment it was taken.
So. chronologically...

1005
01:24:37.140 --> 01:24:42.319
In that reality....
it never left.

1006
01:24:44.705 --> 01:24:47.869
Yes. but you're leaving out
the most important part.

1007
01:24:51.314 --> 01:24:54.149
In order to return the
stones. you have to survive.

1008
01:24:54.196 --> 01:24:57.009
We will. I will. I promise.

1009
01:24:57.666 --> 01:25:00.417
I can't risk this
reality on a promise.

1010
01:25:00.753 --> 01:25:05.534
It's the duty. of the Sorcerer
Supreme to protect the Time Stone.

1011
01:25:06.269 --> 01:25:09.128
Then why the hell did
Strange give it away?

1012
01:25:09.925 --> 01:25:12.143
- What did you say?
- Strange. He gave it away.

1013
01:25:12.182 --> 01:25:13.964
He gave it to Thanos.

1014
01:25:14.244 --> 01:25:16.135
- Willingly?
- Yes.

1015
01:25:19.888 --> 01:25:23.060
- Why?
- I have no idea. Maybe he made a mistake.

1016
01:25:33.513 --> 01:25:34.794
Or I did.

1017
01:25:54.921 --> 01:25:57.608
Strange was meant to
be the best of us.

1018
01:25:57.632 --> 01:26:00.499
So he must've done
it for a reason.

1019
01:26:00.896 --> 01:26:03.239
I fear you might be right.

1020
01:26:07.349 --> 01:26:08.583
Thank you.

1021
01:26:14.753 --> 01:26:16.667
I'm counting on you. Bruce.

1022
01:26:18.605 --> 01:26:19.963
We all are.

1023
01:26:40.102 --> 01:26:41.673
Run diagnostics.

1024
01:26:42.501 --> 01:26:44.337
Show me her memory file.

1025
01:26:46.071 --> 01:26:48.594
Sire. the file appears entangled.

1026
01:26:49.743 --> 01:26:52.024
It was a memory. but not hers.

1027
01:26:52.844 --> 01:26:55.953
There's another consciousness
sharing her network.

1028
01:26:56.289 --> 01:26:57.703
Another Nebula.

1029
01:26:59.844 --> 01:27:01.133
Impossible.

1030
01:27:01.586 --> 01:27:06.992
This duplicate carries a time stamp...
from nine years in the future.

1031
01:27:11.761 --> 01:27:13.815
Where is this other Nebula?

1032
01:27:14.714 --> 01:27:17.479
In our solar system.
On Morag.

1033
01:27:18.394 --> 01:27:21.933
- Can you access her?
- Yes. The two are linked.

1034
01:27:21.964 --> 01:27:26.378
Search the duplicate's
memories. for Infinity Stones.

1035
01:27:30.023 --> 01:27:33.172
And these stones have been in a lot of
different places throughout history.

1036
01:27:33.188 --> 01:27:37.195
Our history. So. not a lot of
convenient spots to just drop in.

1037
01:27:37.219 --> 01:27:40.031
- Which means we have to pick our targets.
- Correct.

1038
01:27:40.056 --> 01:27:41.391
Freeze image.

1039
01:27:43.079 --> 01:27:44.407
Terrans.

1040
01:27:45.164 --> 01:27:46.868
Avengers.

1041
01:27:47.954 --> 01:27:52.118
Unruly wretches. What's
that reflection?

1042
01:27:52.946 --> 01:27:55.501
Amplify this. Maw.

1043
01:27:57.493 --> 01:27:59.149
I don't understand.

1044
01:28:03.555 --> 01:28:08.039
- Two Nebulas.
- No. The same Nebula.

1045
01:28:08.483 --> 01:28:10.366
From two different times.

1046
01:28:11.389 --> 01:28:15.521
Set course for Morag. Scan
the duplicate's memories.

1047
01:28:16.420 --> 01:28:18.959
I want to see everything.

1048
01:28:28.672 --> 01:28:30.658
My ladies. I'll see you after.
Go on.

1049
01:28:46.498 --> 01:28:49.013
- What are you doing?
- Ahh!

1050
01:28:50.427 --> 01:28:53.068
You're better off leaving the
sneaking to your brother.

1051
01:28:53.100 --> 01:28:55.334
Yeah. I was simply just
going for a walk. and uh...

1052
01:28:55.358 --> 01:28:56.757
What are you wearing?

1053
01:28:56.782 --> 01:28:59.123
I always wear this. This
is one of my favorites.

1054
01:29:03.190 --> 01:29:04.650
What's wrong with your eye?

1055
01:29:04.675 --> 01:29:07.823
Oh. my eye. That's... you
remember the Battle of Haroquin?

1056
01:29:07.839 --> 01:29:11.026
When I got hit in the
face with a broadsword?

1057
01:29:14.626 --> 01:29:17.672
You're not the Thor I
know at all. are you?

1058
01:29:17.681 --> 01:29:19.399
Yes. I am.

1059
01:29:19.627 --> 01:29:22.431
The future hasn't been
kind to you. has it?

1060
01:29:22.595 --> 01:29:24.928
I didn't say I'm
from the future.

1061
01:29:25.007 --> 01:29:27.437
I was raised by witches. boy.

1062
01:29:28.343 --> 01:29:31.522
I see with more than
eyes. and you know that.

1063
01:29:32.982 --> 01:29:35.567
I am totally. totally
from the future!

1064
01:29:35.593 --> 01:29:36.633
Yes. you are.

1065
01:29:37.294 --> 01:29:40.099
- I really need to talk to you.
- We can talk.

1066
01:30:04.235 --> 01:30:06.016
His head was over there...

1067
01:30:06.728 --> 01:30:08.392
His body over there...

1068
01:30:10.244 --> 01:30:12.484
What was the point.
I was too late.

1069
01:30:13.539 --> 01:30:15.116
I was just standing there.

1070
01:30:16.437 --> 01:30:19.390
- Some idiot with an ax.
- You're no idiot.

1071
01:30:20.852 --> 01:30:25.359
You're here aren't you? Seeking counsel
from the wisest person in Asgard.

1072
01:30:25.656 --> 01:30:28.219
- I guess. yeah.
- Idiot? No.

1073
01:30:28.336 --> 01:30:32.515
- A failure? Absolutely.
- That's a little bit harsh.

1074
01:30:32.570 --> 01:30:35.265
You do know what
that makes you?

1075
01:30:35.416 --> 01:30:37.727
Just like everyone else.

1076
01:30:37.868 --> 01:30:40.907
I'm not supposed to be
like everyone else. am I?

1077
01:30:41.266 --> 01:30:44.578
Everyone fails at who they
are supposed to be. Thor.

1078
01:30:45.254 --> 01:30:48.359
The measure of a
person. of a hero

1079
01:30:48.443 --> 01:30:51.802
is how well they succeed
at being who they are.

1080
01:30:56.980 --> 01:30:58.800
I really missed you. Mum.

1081
01:31:04.455 --> 01:31:06.415
Thor! I got it!

1082
01:31:06.969 --> 01:31:08.742
Get that rabbit!

1083
01:31:11.501 --> 01:31:14.899
- Ma. I have to tell you something.
- No. son. You don't.

1084
01:31:15.299 --> 01:31:18.126
You're here to repair
your future. not mine.

1085
01:31:18.158 --> 01:31:21.923
- But this is about your future.
- It's none of my business.

1086
01:31:25.244 --> 01:31:26.244
Hey.

1087
01:31:26.399 --> 01:31:27.930
You must be Mom.

1088
01:31:28.735 --> 01:31:30.679
I got the thing. Come
on. we got to move.

1089
01:31:30.704 --> 01:31:34.196
- I wish we had more time.
- This was a gift.

1090
01:31:34.250 --> 01:31:36.976
And you're going to be the
man you're meant to be.

1091
01:31:38.023 --> 01:31:40.968
- I love you. Mom.
- I love you.

1092
01:31:44.210 --> 01:31:45.741
And eat a salad.

1093
01:31:47.312 --> 01:31:49.155
- Come on. We gotta go.
- Goodbye.

1094
01:31:49.171 --> 01:31:51.952
- Three... two...
- No. wait!

1095
01:31:54.968 --> 01:31:56.100
Wh- what am I looking at?

1096
01:31:56.125 --> 01:31:58.444
Oh. sometimes it takes a second.

1097
01:32:07.445 --> 01:32:08.945
I'm still worthy.

1098
01:32:10.336 --> 01:32:11.609
Oh. boy.

1099
01:32:13.187 --> 01:32:15.171
Goodbye. Mom.

1100
01:32:54.314 --> 01:32:55.806
So he's an idiot?

1101
01:33:07.196 --> 01:33:08.383
What's that?

1102
01:33:08.423 --> 01:33:10.039
The tool of a thief.

1103
01:33:18.133 --> 01:33:19.666
Whoa. whoa.
whoa. whoa...

1104
01:33:20.136 --> 01:33:23.840
This is the part where spikes come out.
with skeletons on the end and everything...

1105
01:33:23.865 --> 01:33:24.778
What are you talking about?

1106
01:33:24.803 --> 01:33:27.429
When you break into a place called
the temple of the Power Stone.

1107
01:33:27.454 --> 01:33:31.266
There's gonna be a bunch of booby
traps--- Okay. All right. Go ahead.

1108
01:34:04.413 --> 01:34:06.186
I wasn't always like this.

1109
01:34:07.089 --> 01:34:08.295
Me either.

1110
01:34:09.620 --> 01:34:11.827
But we work with
what we got. right?

1111
01:34:15.053 --> 01:34:16.155
Sync up.

1112
01:34:18.358 --> 01:34:20.772
Three.. two.. one...

1113
01:34:33.697 --> 01:34:35.173
You murdered trillions!

1114
01:34:35.198 --> 01:34:36.933
You should be grateful.

1115
01:34:38.597 --> 01:34:41.605
- Where are the stones?
- Gone.

1116
01:34:41.995 --> 01:34:45.675
- Reduced to atoms.
- You used them two days ago.

1117
01:34:45.765 --> 01:34:50.756
I used the stones to destroy the stones.
It nearly killed me.

1118
01:34:50.913 --> 01:34:54.975
But the work is done.
It always will be.

1119
01:34:56.155 --> 01:34:59.936
I am inevitable.

1120
01:35:00.913 --> 01:35:06.780
- What did you do to them?
- Nothing. Yet.

1121
01:35:08.028 --> 01:35:11.910
They're not trying to stop something
I'm going to do in our time.

1122
01:35:12.385 --> 01:35:15.924
They're trying to undo something
I've already done in theirs.

1123
01:35:16.174 --> 01:35:17.728
The stones...

1124
01:35:18.673 --> 01:35:20.470
I found them all.

1125
01:35:22.156 --> 01:35:23.406
I won.

1126
01:35:24.469 --> 01:35:27.441
Tipped the cosmic
scales to balance.

1127
01:35:31.597 --> 01:35:33.003
This is your future.

1128
01:35:33.566 --> 01:35:35.050
It's my destiny.

1129
01:35:36.792 --> 01:35:40.768
My father is many things. A
liar is not one of them.

1130
01:35:44.450 --> 01:35:45.795
Thank you. Daughter.

1131
01:35:46.154 --> 01:35:49.248
Perhaps I treated
you too harshly...

1132
01:35:53.251 --> 01:35:56.017
And that. is destiny fulfilled.

1133
01:35:56.728 --> 01:36:00.017
Sire. your Daughter...

1134
01:36:01.625 --> 01:36:02.625
No...

1135
01:36:03.078 --> 01:36:04.366
...is a traitor.

1136
01:36:04.391 --> 01:36:09.047
That's not me. It's not. I could never...
I would never betray you. Never.

1137
01:36:16.100 --> 01:36:17.310
I know.

1138
01:36:18.137 --> 01:36:20.856
And you'll have the
chance to prove it.

1139
01:36:27.743 --> 01:36:28.743
No...

1140
01:36:29.305 --> 01:36:30.633
He knows!

1141
01:36:34.914 --> 01:36:37.671
Barton? Barton. come in.

1142
01:36:37.734 --> 01:36:41.960
Romanoff? Come in. we have a problem.
Come on!

1143
01:36:42.360 --> 01:36:43.742
Come in. we have a prob....

1144
01:36:43.969 --> 01:36:45.820
Thanos knows.

1145
01:36:45.930 --> 01:36:47.235
Thanos...

1146
01:37:01.277 --> 01:37:02.277
Cap...

1147
01:37:03.863 --> 01:37:05.929
Sorry. buddy.
We got a problem.

1148
01:37:05.972 --> 01:37:08.464
Huh. Yeah. we do.

1149
01:37:08.730 --> 01:37:11.011
- Well. what are we gonna do now?
- You know what. give me a break. Steve.

1150
01:37:11.036 --> 01:37:12.723
I just got hit in the
head with a Hulk.

1151
01:37:12.857 --> 01:37:15.801
You said that we had one shot.
This. this was our shot.

1152
01:37:15.826 --> 01:37:18.493
We shot it. It's shot. Six stones or nothing.
Six stones or nothing.

1153
01:37:18.518 --> 01:37:20.603
You're repeating yourself. you know that?
You're repeating yourself.

1154
01:37:20.628 --> 01:37:22.408
You're repeating yourself.
You're repeating yourself.

1155
01:37:22.433 --> 01:37:23.316
- No!
- Come on.

1156
01:37:23.341 --> 01:37:25.637
You never wanted a time heist. you
went on board with the time heist...

1157
01:37:25.662 --> 01:37:27.028
- I dropped the ball.
- You ruined the time heist.

1158
01:37:27.053 --> 01:37:28.269
- Is that what I did?
- Yeah!

1159
01:37:28.294 --> 01:37:30.206
Are there any other options
with the Tesseract?

1160
01:37:30.215 --> 01:37:31.949
No. no. no. There's
no other options.

1161
01:37:31.996 --> 01:37:34.121
There's no do-overs. We're
not going anywhere else.

1162
01:37:34.152 --> 01:37:36.596
We have one particle left. Each.

1163
01:37:36.621 --> 01:37:40.285
That's it. alright? We use that...
Bye. bye. You're not going home.

1164
01:37:40.328 --> 01:37:42.516
Yeah. well if we don't try...

1165
01:37:42.573 --> 01:37:44.360
then no one else is
going home. either.

1166
01:37:44.385 --> 01:37:45.540
I got it.

1167
01:37:45.938 --> 01:37:50.297
There's another way. To retake the
Tesseract and acquire new particles.

1168
01:37:51.071 --> 01:37:54.868
We'll stroll down memory lane.
Military installation. Garden State.

1169
01:37:58.539 --> 01:37:59.929
  Why were they both there?

1170
01:37:59.954 --> 01:38:03.164
They were there at a...I've
a vaguely exact idea.

1171
01:38:03.188 --> 01:38:03.984
How vague?

1172
01:38:04.040 --> 01:38:05.438
What are you talking about?
Where are we going?

1173
01:38:05.463 --> 01:38:06.666
- I know for a fact they were there...
- Who's they?

1174
01:38:06.689 --> 01:38:09.414
- What are we doing?
- And I know how I know.

1175
01:38:10.312 --> 01:38:12.374
Guys. what's up? What is it?

1176
01:38:12.539 --> 01:38:14.326
Well. it looks like
we're improvising.

1177
01:38:14.351 --> 01:38:15.849
- Right.
- What are we improvising?

1178
01:38:15.874 --> 01:38:17.968
Scott. get this back
to the compound.

1179
01:38:17.993 --> 01:38:18.703
Suit up.

1180
01:38:18.735 --> 01:38:19.882
What's in New Jersey?

1181
01:38:19.907 --> 01:38:21.781
- 0-4. 0-4...
- Uhh. 0-7.

1182
01:38:21.806 --> 01:38:22.875
- 0-7.
- Excuse me...

1183
01:38:22.900 --> 01:38:24.384
1-9-7-0.

1184
01:38:24.939 --> 01:38:29.290
- Are you sure?
- Cap. Captain. Steve. sorry.

1185
01:38:29.654 --> 01:38:32.552
America. Rogers. Look.
if you do this.

1186
01:38:32.587 --> 01:38:35.602
and this doesn't work.
you're not coming back.

1187
01:38:36.446 --> 01:38:38.646
Thanks for the pep
talk. pissant.

1188
01:38:39.259 --> 01:38:40.524
You trust me?

1189
01:38:41.039 --> 01:38:42.165
I do.

1190
01:38:43.642 --> 01:38:44.899
Your call.

1191
01:38:45.813 --> 01:38:47.188
Here we go.

1192
01:39:03.329 --> 01:39:04.775
Hey. man!

1193
01:39:05.075 --> 01:39:06.605
Make love. not war!

1194
01:39:13.284 --> 01:39:15.926
Clearly. you weren't
actually born here. right?

1195
01:39:15.951 --> 01:39:17.565
The idea of me was.

1196
01:39:18.315 --> 01:39:20.877
Right. Well. imagine
you're SHIELD. running a

1197
01:39:20.902 --> 01:39:23.791
quasi-fascistic
intelligence organization.

1198
01:39:24.839 --> 01:39:25.978
Where do you hide it?

1199
01:39:26.438 --> 01:39:27.651
In plain sight.

1200
01:39:56.623 --> 01:39:58.097
Good luck on your
mission. Captain.

1201
01:39:58.122 --> 01:40:00.365
Good luck on your
project. doctor.

1202
01:40:04.022 --> 01:40:05.365
You're new here?

1203
01:40:07.584 --> 01:40:08.787
Not exactly.

1204
01:40:24.258 --> 01:40:25.468
Gotcha.

1205
01:40:43.275 --> 01:40:44.658
Back in the game.

1206
01:40:47.666 --> 01:40:49.424
Arnim. you in there?

1207
01:40:49.736 --> 01:40:50.884
Arnim?

1208
01:40:56.111 --> 01:40:57.111
Hey!

1209
01:40:57.486 --> 01:40:59.407
The door's this way. pal.

1210
01:41:00.470 --> 01:41:01.525
Oh. yeah.

1211
01:41:01.792 --> 01:41:03.564
I'm looking for Dr. Zola.
Have you seen him?

1212
01:41:03.589 --> 01:41:07.424
Yeah. no. Dr. Zol... No.
I haven't seen a soul.

1213
01:41:08.653 --> 01:41:09.840
Pardon me.

1214
01:41:10.754 --> 01:41:12.254
Do I know you?

1215
01:41:13.699 --> 01:41:15.745
No. sir. I'm. a...

1216
01:41:16.168 --> 01:41:17.660
visitor from MIT.

1217
01:41:17.800 --> 01:41:19.519
Huh. MIT.

1218
01:41:20.128 --> 01:41:21.433
Got a name?

1219
01:41:21.824 --> 01:41:22.887
Howard.

1220
01:41:22.912 --> 01:41:24.527
Well that'll be
easy to remember.

1221
01:41:24.543 --> 01:41:26.019
Howard...

1222
01:41:26.683 --> 01:41:27.894
...Potts.

1223
01:41:27.919 --> 01:41:29.878
Well. I'm Howard Stark.

1224
01:41:30.510 --> 01:41:31.347
Hi.

1225
01:41:31.355 --> 01:41:32.690
Shit. Now. don't pull it.

1226
01:41:32.746 --> 01:41:33.746
Yeah...

1227
01:41:35.456 --> 01:41:37.605
You look a little green around
the gills there. Potts.

1228
01:41:37.660 --> 01:41:39.534
I'm fine. Just. long hours.

1229
01:41:40.066 --> 01:41:41.761
Wanna get some air?

1230
01:41:44.269 --> 01:41:47.011
- Hello. Potts.
- Yeah. That would be swell.

1231
01:41:47.081 --> 01:41:48.464
- That way.
- Okay.

1232
01:41:48.683 --> 01:41:50.261
Need your briefcase?

1233
01:41:55.011 --> 01:41:57.370
You're not one of
those. are ya. Potts?

1234
01:42:03.221 --> 01:42:04.963
- Hello.
- Dr. Pym?

1235
01:42:04.988 --> 01:42:07.629
That would be the number
that you called. Yes.

1236
01:42:07.654 --> 01:42:10.051
This is Capt. Stevens
from shipping.

1237
01:42:10.076 --> 01:42:12.628
- We have a package for you.
- Bring it up.

1238
01:42:12.653 --> 01:42:15.067
Well. that's the thing. sir.
We can't.

1239
01:42:15.933 --> 01:42:18.558
I'm confused. I thought
that was your job.

1240
01:42:18.706 --> 01:42:21.987
Well. it's just... Sir.
the box is glowing and.

1241
01:42:22.012 --> 01:42:24.699
to be honest. some of our mail
guys aren't feeling that great.

1242
01:42:24.724 --> 01:42:26.472
They didn't know
better. did they?

1243
01:42:26.497 --> 01:42:29.082
Yeah. they did. You
better get down here.

1244
01:42:29.677 --> 01:42:32.208
Excuse me. Out of the way!

1245
01:42:58.779 --> 01:43:02.224
So. flowers and sauerkraut. You
got a big date tonight?

1246
01:43:02.908 --> 01:43:04.572
My wife's expecting.

1247
01:43:04.846 --> 01:43:07.440
And. uh... Too much
time in the office.

1248
01:43:09.346 --> 01:43:11.680
- Congratulations.
- Thanks. Hold this. will you?

1249
01:43:11.705 --> 01:43:13.314
Yeah. sure.

1250
01:43:14.076 --> 01:43:16.373
- How far along is she?
- I don't know... uh...

1251
01:43:17.972 --> 01:43:21.011
She's at the point where she can't
stand the sound of my chewing.

1252
01:43:21.081 --> 01:43:24.073
I guess I'll be eating
dinner in the pantry again.

1253
01:43:25.087 --> 01:43:26.425
I have a little girl.

1254
01:43:26.450 --> 01:43:30.270
A girl would be nice. Less of a chance
she'd turn out exactly like me.

1255
01:43:30.818 --> 01:43:32.393
What'd be so awful about that?

1256
01:43:32.418 --> 01:43:35.747
Let's just say that the greater
good has rarely outweighed

1257
01:43:36.503 --> 01:43:38.690
my own self-interests.

1258
01:43:41.589 --> 01:43:43.979
- And you've never seen these 2 men before?
- No. I've got an eye for this.

1259
01:43:44.004 --> 01:43:45.896
- The 2 of them looked fishy.
- Can you describe them?

1260
01:43:45.921 --> 01:43:49.272
- Well. one of them had a hippie beard.
- Hippie? Like Bee Gees or Mungo Jerry?

1261
01:43:49.297 --> 01:43:50.361
Definitely Mungo Jerry.

1262
01:43:50.386 --> 01:43:52.565
Yeah. this is Chesler. I
need every available MPs

1263
01:43:52.590 --> 01:43:54.839
on sub-level 6. We have
a potential breach.

1264
01:44:56.632 --> 01:44:58.334
So. where are you
at with names?

1265
01:44:58.359 --> 01:45:01.413
Well. if it's a boy.
my wife likes Almanzo.

1266
01:45:02.359 --> 01:45:04.639
Might wanna let that stew on.
You got time.

1267
01:45:06.469 --> 01:45:08.449
Let me ask you a question.

1268
01:45:08.903 --> 01:45:11.067
When your kid was born...

1269
01:45:11.353 --> 01:45:14.418
- were you nervous?
- Wildly. Yeah.

1270
01:45:14.442 --> 01:45:15.824
Did you feel qualified?

1271
01:45:15.849 --> 01:45:19.402
Like you had any idea how to
successfully operate that thing?

1272
01:45:19.595 --> 01:45:22.673
I literally pieced it
together as I went along.

1273
01:45:22.728 --> 01:45:25.329
I thought about what
my Dad did. and...

1274
01:45:25.532 --> 01:45:28.430
My old man. he never met a problem
he couldn't solve with a belt.

1275
01:45:28.555 --> 01:45:30.649
I thought my Dad
was tough on me.

1276
01:45:30.692 --> 01:45:33.679
And now. looking back. I just
remember the good stuff. you know.

1277
01:45:33.735 --> 01:45:36.866
- He did drop the odd pearl.
- Yeah? Like what?

1278
01:45:37.776 --> 01:45:40.526
"No amount of money ever
bought a second of time."

1279
01:45:41.589 --> 01:45:42.980
Smart guy.

1280
01:45:43.004 --> 01:45:44.424
He did his best.

1281
01:45:45.861 --> 01:45:47.627
Let me tell you. That
kid's not even here yet

1282
01:45:47.652 --> 01:45:49.979
and. there's nothing I
wouldn't do for him.

1283
01:45:58.270 --> 01:45:59.707
Good to meet you. Potts.

1284
01:46:00.669 --> 01:46:02.895
Yeah. Howard...

1285
01:46:03.790 --> 01:46:05.797
Everything's gonna be all right.

1286
01:46:08.002 --> 01:46:11.510
Thank you for everything...

1287
01:46:11.768 --> 01:46:14.353
...you've done for
this country.

1288
01:46:17.111 --> 01:46:18.275
Jarvis.

1289
01:46:21.971 --> 01:46:23.641
Have we ever met that guy?

1290
01:46:25.924 --> 01:46:27.369


1291
01:46:29.893 --> 01:46:31.720
Seems very familiar.

1292
01:46:32.510 --> 01:46:34.056
Weird beard. though.

1293
01:46:42.186 --> 01:46:44.922
- You're weak.
- I'm you.

1294
01:47:02.362 --> 01:47:03.822
You can stop this.

1295
01:47:04.572 --> 01:47:06.377
You know you want to.

1296
01:47:07.447 --> 01:47:10.047
Did you see what
happens in the future?

1297
01:47:10.721 --> 01:47:13.205
Thanos finds the Soul Stone.

1298
01:47:14.619 --> 01:47:16.752
You wanna know
how he does that?

1299
01:47:17.846 --> 01:47:22.603
You wanna know. what
he does to you?

1300
01:47:22.751 --> 01:47:24.119
That's enough.

1301
01:47:36.248 --> 01:47:37.693
You disgust me.

1302
01:47:39.154 --> 01:47:43.802
But. that doesn't
mean you're useless.

1303
01:48:05.878 --> 01:48:07.417
How do I look?

1304
01:48:14.168 --> 01:48:15.168
Wow...

1305
01:48:15.972 --> 01:48:18.315
Under different circumstances.

1306
01:48:19.172 --> 01:48:21.409
this would be totally awesome.

1307
01:48:33.326 --> 01:48:36.451
I bet the raccoon didn't
have to climb a mountain.

1308
01:48:36.582 --> 01:48:38.566
Technically. he's not
a raccoon. you know.

1309
01:48:38.591 --> 01:48:40.209
Whatever. He eats garbage.

1310
01:48:40.503 --> 01:48:41.503
Welcome.

1311
01:48:44.855 --> 01:48:47.573
Natasha. daughter of Ivan.

1312
01:48:48.572 --> 01:48:51.502
Clint. son of Edith.

1313
01:48:57.685 --> 01:48:58.801
Who are you?

1314
01:48:59.817 --> 01:49:02.012
Consider me a guide.

1315
01:49:02.353 --> 01:49:05.958
To you. and to all who
seek the Soul Stone.

1316
01:49:06.064 --> 01:49:09.493
Okay. You tell us where it is.
Then we'll be on our way.

1317
01:49:13.259 --> 01:49:15.211
If only it were that easy.

1318
01:49:27.735 --> 01:49:30.657
What you seek lies
in front of you...

1319
01:49:32.665 --> 01:49:34.485
...as does what you fear.

1320
01:49:40.160 --> 01:49:41.760
The stone is down there.

1321
01:49:42.551 --> 01:49:43.707
For one of you.

1322
01:49:44.895 --> 01:49:46.090
For the other...

1323
01:49:49.098 --> 01:49:53.551
In order to take the stone. you
must lose that which you love.

1324
01:49:55.518 --> 01:49:57.698
An everlasting exchange.

1325
01:49:59.768 --> 01:50:02.791
A soul. for a soul.

1326
01:50:06.268 --> 01:50:07.674
How's it going?

1327
01:50:11.307 --> 01:50:12.307
Jesus...

1328
01:50:12.947 --> 01:50:15.088
Maybe he's making this shit up.

1329
01:50:15.315 --> 01:50:18.721
No. I don't think so.

1330
01:50:19.510 --> 01:50:21.557
Why. 'cause he knows
your Daddy's name?

1331
01:50:23.198 --> 01:50:24.314
I didn't.

1332
01:50:25.509 --> 01:50:27.635
Thanos left here with the stone

1333
01:50:28.729 --> 01:50:32.213
without his daughter.
It's not a coincidence.

1334
01:50:33.604 --> 01:50:34.604
Yeah.

1335
01:50:36.658 --> 01:50:38.729
Whatever it takes.

1336
01:50:43.268 --> 01:50:44.549
Whatever it takes.

1337
01:50:49.072 --> 01:50:53.018
If we don't get that stone.
billions of people stay dead.

1338
01:50:56.748 --> 01:50:59.294
Then I guess we both
know who it's gotta be.

1339
01:50:59.655 --> 01:51:01.107
I guess we do.

1340
01:51:07.885 --> 01:51:12.307
I'm starting to think. we've been
different people here. Natasha.

1341
01:51:12.721 --> 01:51:16.127
For the last five years I've been trying
to do one thing: Get to right here.

1342
01:51:16.205 --> 01:51:18.478
That's all it's been about.
Bringing everybody back.

1343
01:51:18.503 --> 01:51:23.049
- Oh. don't you get all decent on me now.
- What. you think I wanna do it?

1344
01:51:23.456 --> 01:51:25.460
I'm trying to save
your life. you idiot.

1345
01:51:25.485 --> 01:51:27.632
Yeah well. I don't want
you to. because I...

1346
01:51:28.623 --> 01:51:30.823
Natasha. you know
what I've done.

1347
01:51:32.295 --> 01:51:34.560
You know what I've become.

1348
01:51:36.365 --> 01:51:39.044
I don't judge people on
their worst mistakes.

1349
01:51:43.232 --> 01:51:44.568
Maybe you should.

1350
01:51:45.443 --> 01:51:46.537
You didn't.

1351
01:51:52.937 --> 01:51:55.358
You're a pain in my
ass. you know that?

1352
01:52:06.242 --> 01:52:07.382
Okay.

1353
01:52:09.367 --> 01:52:10.601
You win.

1354
01:52:17.260 --> 01:52:19.060
Tell my family I love them.

1355
01:52:22.023 --> 01:52:23.578
You tell them yourself.

1356
01:52:56.331 --> 01:52:57.456
Damn you!

1357
01:53:13.662 --> 01:53:14.905
Let me go.

1358
01:53:16.800 --> 01:53:17.800
No.

1359
01:53:19.861 --> 01:53:20.987
Please. no.

1360
01:53:23.883 --> 01:53:25.476
It's okay.

1361
01:53:28.163 --> 01:53:29.199
Please...

1362
01:55:13.096 --> 01:55:14.393
Did we get them all?

1363
01:55:15.010 --> 01:55:17.408
You telling me this'll
actually work?

1364
01:55:22.125 --> 01:55:23.687
Clint. where's Nat?

1365
01:55:52.872 --> 01:55:54.805
Do we know if she had family?

1366
01:55:54.904 --> 01:55:57.068
Yeah. Us.

1367
01:55:58.638 --> 01:55:59.786
What?

1368
01:56:02.060 --> 01:56:03.341
I just asked him a question...

1369
01:56:03.366 --> 01:56:05.489
Yeah. you're acting like she's dead.
Why are we acting like she's dead?

1370
01:56:05.514 --> 01:56:07.421
We have the stones. right?
As long as we have

1371
01:56:07.446 --> 01:56:09.780
the stones. Cap. we can bring
her back. isn't that right?

1372
01:56:09.805 --> 01:56:12.148
So stop this shit. We're the
Avengers. get it together.

1373
01:56:12.173 --> 01:56:13.983
We can't get her back.

1374
01:56:16.710 --> 01:56:20.774
- Wha- what?
- It can't be undone. It can't.

1375
01:56:23.378 --> 01:56:27.240
I'm sorry. No offense. but you're
a very earthly being. Okay?

1376
01:56:27.265 --> 01:56:30.656
We're talking about space magic.
And "can't" seems very () don't you think?

1377
01:56:30.687 --> 01:56:33.687
Look. I know that I'm way
outside my paygrade here.

1378
01:56:33.695 --> 01:56:35.257
But she still isn't
here. is she?

1379
01:56:35.282 --> 01:56:39.210
- Now that's my point.
- It can't be undone.

1380
01:56:39.718 --> 01:56:43.069
Or that's at least what the.
great floating guy had to say.

1381
01:56:43.093 --> 01:56:44.740
Maybe you wanna go talk to him?
Okay?

1382
01:56:44.765 --> 01:56:48.202
Go grab your hammer. and you
go fly and you talk to him.

1383
01:56:56.213 --> 01:56:58.212
It was supposed to be me.

1384
01:57:00.869 --> 01:57:04.916
She sacrificed her life for that
goddamned stone. She bet her life on it.

1385
01:57:09.466 --> 01:57:11.372
She's not coming back.

1386
01:57:13.692 --> 01:57:16.520
We have to make it worth it.
We have to.

1387
01:57:18.549 --> 01:57:19.666
We will.

1388
01:57:44.928 --> 01:57:46.006
Boom!

1389
01:57:51.514 --> 01:57:53.451
All right. The glove's ready.

1390
01:57:53.888 --> 01:57:56.622
Question is. who's gonna
snap their freaking fingers?

1391
01:57:57.035 --> 01:57:58.035
I'll do it.

1392
01:57:58.622 --> 01:57:59.622
It's okay.

1393
01:57:59.646 --> 01:58:01.419
- No. no. no. no. Stop. Stop.
- Hey. hey...

1394
01:58:01.435 --> 01:58:02.411
Thor. just wait.

1395
01:58:02.436 --> 01:58:04.646
We haven't decided who's
gonna put that on yet.

1396
01:58:05.139 --> 01:58:08.045
I'm sorry. What. were you just sitting
around waiting for the right opportunity?

1397
01:58:08.092 --> 01:58:09.404
We should at least discuss it.

1398
01:58:09.413 --> 01:58:13.256
Look. us sitting here staring at that
thing is not gonna bring everybody back.

1399
01:58:14.284 --> 01:58:17.459
I'm the strongest Avenger. okay? So
this responsibility falls upon me.

1400
01:58:17.484 --> 01:58:22.648
It's my duty. It's not that... It's...
stop it! Just let me.

1401
01:58:25.146 --> 01:58:28.802
Just let me do it. Just
let me do something good.

1402
01:58:28.827 --> 01:58:29.646
- Something great.
- Look...

1403
01:58:29.662 --> 01:58:31.599
It's not just the fact that
that glove is channeling

1404
01:58:31.624 --> 01:58:34.326
enough energy to light up a
continent. I'm telling you

1405
01:58:34.350 --> 01:58:35.350
you're in no condition.

1406
01:58:35.389 --> 01:58:38.678
What do you think is coursing
through my veins right now?

1407
01:58:38.703 --> 01:58:39.920
Cheez Whiz?

1408
01:58:42.602 --> 01:58:44.271
- Lightning.
- Yeah.

1409
01:58:44.329 --> 01:58:46.242
Lightning won't help you. pal.

1410
01:58:46.306 --> 01:58:47.680
It's gotta be me.

1411
01:58:49.391 --> 01:58:52.875
You saw what those stones did to Thanos.
It almost killed him.

1412
01:58:54.852 --> 01:58:56.672
None of you could survive.

1413
01:58:57.123 --> 01:58:59.068
How do we know you will?

1414
01:58:59.084 --> 01:59:02.834
I don't. But the
radiation's mostly gamma.

1415
01:59:06.230 --> 01:59:07.582
It's like...

1416
01:59:09.886 --> 01:59:11.621
I was meant for this.

1417
01:59:30.651 --> 01:59:32.480
Good to go. yeah?

1418
01:59:34.246 --> 01:59:35.667
Let's do it.

1419
01:59:35.808 --> 01:59:37.885
You remember everyone
Thanos snapped away five

1420
01:59:37.910 --> 01:59:40.746
years ago and just bringing
them back to now. today.

1421
01:59:41.455 --> 01:59:43.845
Don't change anything
from the last five years.

1422
01:59:43.994 --> 01:59:44.994
Got it.

1423
02:00:01.837 --> 02:00:04.610
Friday. do me a favor and
activate protocol 8.

1424
02:00:04.650 --> 02:00:05.797
Yes. boss.

1425
02:00:14.462 --> 02:00:16.102
Everybody comes home.

1426
02:00:39.480 --> 02:00:42.847
- Take it off. Take it off!
- No. wait. Bruce. are you okay?

1427
02:00:43.472 --> 02:00:44.815
Talk to me. Banner.

1428
02:00:48.379 --> 02:00:50.879
I'm okay. I'm okay.

1429
02:01:22.318 --> 02:01:23.339
Bruce!

1430
02:01:24.815 --> 02:01:26.527
Don't move him.

1431
02:01:33.610 --> 02:01:36.383
- Did it work?
- Worth a shot. It's over. It's okay.

1432
02:02:21.926 --> 02:02:22.871
Honey.

1433
02:02:24.114 --> 02:02:25.114
Honey.

1434
02:02:26.419 --> 02:02:27.419
Guys...

1435
02:02:30.218 --> 02:02:31.936
I think it worked!

1436
02:03:13.332 --> 02:03:15.628
I can't breathe. I can't breathe!
I can't breathe.

1437
02:03:16.854 --> 02:03:19.205
Canopy. Canopy. Canopy.

1438
02:03:25.628 --> 02:03:27.902
Rhodey. Rocket. get outta here!

1439
02:03:28.477 --> 02:03:30.008
Hurry up! Hurry up!

1440
02:03:30.320 --> 02:03:31.415
Come on!

1441
02:03:41.500 --> 02:03:42.890
Rhodey!

1442
02:03:51.079 --> 02:03:54.883
Mayday. mayday! Does anybody copy? We're
in the lower level. it's flooding!

1443
02:03:54.915 --> 02:03:58.448
- What?
- We're drowning! Does anybody copy? Mayday!

1444
02:03:58.567 --> 02:04:02.528
Wait! I'm here! I'm
here. can you hear me?

1445
02:04:22.099 --> 02:04:23.099
Cap?

1446
02:05:07.700 --> 02:05:08.700
Daughter.

1447
02:05:08.763 --> 02:05:10.075
Yes. Father.

1448
02:05:12.005 --> 02:05:15.255
So. this is the future.
Well done.

1449
02:05:15.763 --> 02:05:19.309
Thank you. Father. They
suspected nothing.

1450
02:05:21.396 --> 02:05:23.614
The arrogant never do.

1451
02:05:25.693 --> 02:05:26.693
Go.

1452
02:05:27.653 --> 02:05:30.199
Find the stones.
Bring them to me.

1453
02:05:30.465 --> 02:05:31.856
What will you do?

1454
02:05:33.325 --> 02:05:34.450
Wait.

1455
02:06:00.434 --> 02:06:02.324
Tell me something.

1456
02:06:02.980 --> 02:06:07.362
In the future. what
happens to you and me?

1457
02:06:09.903 --> 02:06:11.379
I tried to kill you.

1458
02:06:13.262 --> 02:06:14.433
Several times.

1459
02:06:15.895 --> 02:06:19.152
But eventually.
we become friends.

1460
02:06:21.387 --> 02:06:23.097
We become sisters.

1461
02:06:30.617 --> 02:06:31.850
Come on.

1462
02:06:33.742 --> 02:06:35.211
We can stop him.

1463
02:06:43.808 --> 02:06:45.408
Come on. buddy. Wake up.

1464
02:06:45.605 --> 02:06:47.003
That's my man.

1465
02:06:48.097 --> 02:06:50.581
You lose this again.
I'm keeping it.

1466
02:06:53.519 --> 02:06:54.886
What happened?

1467
02:06:55.071 --> 02:06:57.219
We messed with time.
It tends to mess back.

1468
02:06:57.244 --> 02:06:58.244
You'll see.

1469
02:07:20.021 --> 02:07:21.872
What's he been doing?

1470
02:07:23.387 --> 02:07:24.973
Absolutely nothing.

1471
02:07:26.677 --> 02:07:28.192
Where are the stones?

1472
02:07:28.715 --> 02:07:30.676
Lost somewhere under all this.

1473
02:07:31.896 --> 02:07:34.200
All I know is he
doesn't have them.

1474
02:07:34.528 --> 02:07:36.121
So we keep it that way.

1475
02:07:36.146 --> 02:07:38.599
- You know it's a trap. right?
- Yeah...

1476
02:07:39.294 --> 02:07:40.770
I don't much care.

1477
02:07:41.333 --> 02:07:42.333
Good.

1478
02:07:43.489 --> 02:07:46.089
Just as long as we're
all in agreement.

1479
02:07:55.755 --> 02:07:58.022
Let's kill him
properly this time.

1480
02:08:07.045 --> 02:08:09.778
You could not live
with your own failure.

1481
02:08:11.498 --> 02:08:13.264
Where did that bring you?

1482
02:08:16.398 --> 02:08:17.719
Back to me.

1483
02:08:21.648 --> 02:08:24.250
I thought by eliminating
half of life.

1484
02:08:25.069 --> 02:08:27.334
the other half would thrive.

1485
02:08:27.702 --> 02:08:32.210
But you've shown me.
that's impossible.

1486
02:08:33.839 --> 02:08:37.222
And as long as there are those
that remember what was.

1487
02:08:37.247 --> 02:08:42.489
there will always be those that
are unable to accept what can be.

1488
02:08:43.184 --> 02:08:44.598
They will resist.

1489
02:08:44.895 --> 02:08:47.095
Yep. We're all
kinds of stubborn.

1490
02:08:47.825 --> 02:08:49.450
I'm thankful.

1491
02:08:51.614 --> 02:08:55.520
Because now. I know
what I must do.

1492
02:08:56.192 --> 02:09:01.449
I will shred this universe
down to its last atom.

1493
02:09:02.231 --> 02:09:03.645
And then...

1494
02:09:03.970 --> 02:09:08.860
With the stones you've collected
for me. create a new one.

1495
02:09:09.392 --> 02:09:11.189
Teeming with life.

1496
02:09:11.550 --> 02:09:16.206
but knows not what it has lost
but only what it has been given.

1497
02:09:18.970 --> 02:09:20.579
A grateful universe.

1498
02:09:21.101 --> 02:09:22.571
Born out of blood.

1499
02:09:22.728 --> 02:09:24.399
They'll never know it.

1500
02:09:25.430 --> 02:09:28.097
Because you won't be
alive to tell them.

1501
02:09:43.327 --> 02:09:44.936
See you on the other side. man.

1502
02:09:46.562 --> 02:09:48.795
Hang on! I'm coming!

1503
02:10:34.712 --> 02:10:36.197
Oh. hey...

1504
02:10:36.252 --> 02:10:37.955
I know you.

1505
02:10:41.189 --> 02:10:44.423
Father. I have the stones.

1506
02:10:44.502 --> 02:10:45.502
What?!

1507
02:10:46.728 --> 02:10:47.837
Stop.

1508
02:10:52.789 --> 02:10:54.609
You're betraying us?

1509
02:11:00.313 --> 02:11:02.180
You don't have to do this.

1510
02:11:04.446 --> 02:11:07.367
I am... this.

1511
02:11:07.399 --> 02:11:09.250
No. you're not.

1512
02:11:09.414 --> 02:11:11.461
You've seen what we become.

1513
02:11:17.504 --> 02:11:18.958
Nebula. listen to her.

1514
02:11:21.310 --> 02:11:22.583
You can change.

1515
02:11:28.761 --> 02:11:30.113
He won't let me.

1516
02:11:31.886 --> 02:11:32.886
No!

1517
02:11:52.132 --> 02:11:54.132
Okay. Thor. Hit me.

1518
02:12:10.093 --> 02:12:11.601
Boss. wake up.

1519
02:13:02.683 --> 02:13:03.917
I knew it!

1520
02:14:26.721 --> 02:14:29.057
In all my years of conquest...

1521
02:14:30.323 --> 02:14:31.565
violence...

1522
02:14:33.276 --> 02:14:34.463
slaughter...

1523
02:14:36.362 --> 02:14:37.995
It was never personal.

1524
02:14:41.433 --> 02:14:43.159
But I'll tell you now...

1525
02:14:45.600 --> 02:14:48.133
what I'm about to do
to your stubborn.

1526
02:14:48.944 --> 02:14:51.170
annoying little planet...

1527
02:14:53.412 --> 02:14:58.216
I'm gonna enjoy it.
Very. very much.

1528
02:16:02.633 --> 02:16:04.140
Cap. you hear me?

1529
02:16:09.629 --> 02:16:11.988
Cap. it's Sam.
Can you hear me?

1530
02:16:16.226 --> 02:16:17.477
On your left.

1531
02:17:43.038 --> 02:17:44.405
Is that everyone?

1532
02:17:44.702 --> 02:17:46.233
What. you wanted more?

1533
02:18:13.336 --> 02:18:14.781
Avengers...

1534
02:18:20.255 --> 02:18:21.512
... assemble.

1535
02:19:18.268 --> 02:19:19.783
No. no. Give me that.

1536
02:19:19.821 --> 02:19:21.393
You have the little one.

1537
02:19:34.921 --> 02:19:35.921
Hey!

1538
02:19:36.835 --> 02:19:37.866
Holy cow.

1539
02:19:37.914 --> 02:19:41.132
You will not believe what's been going on.
Do you remember when we were in space?

1540
02:19:41.157 --> 02:19:44.866
And I got all dusty? I must've passed
out. 'cause I woke up. and you were gone.

1541
02:19:44.891 --> 02:19:46.859
But Doctor Strange was there. right?
He was like.

1542
02:19:46.884 --> 02:19:48.761
"It's been five years.
Come on. they need us!"

1543
02:19:48.786 --> 02:19:51.292
And then he started doing the yellow
sparkly thing that he does all the time...

1544
02:19:51.317 --> 02:19:53.027
What are you doing?

1545
02:19:57.637 --> 02:19:58.793
This is nice.

1546
02:20:20.962 --> 02:20:22.220
Gamora?

1547
02:20:31.229 --> 02:20:32.823
I thought I lost you.

1548
02:20:37.612 --> 02:20:40.346
Don't... touch... me!

1549
02:20:43.501 --> 02:20:45.086
You missed the first time...

1550
02:20:45.657 --> 02:20:48.188
then you got them
both the second time.

1551
02:20:49.783 --> 02:20:52.055
This is the one? Seriously?

1552
02:20:52.124 --> 02:20:54.304
The choices were him. or a tree.

1553
02:21:04.954 --> 02:21:08.273
Cap. what do you want me to
do with this damn thing?

1554
02:21:10.243 --> 02:21:12.602
Get those stones as
far away as possible!

1555
02:21:12.618 --> 02:21:13.735
No!

1556
02:21:14.743 --> 02:21:17.041
We need to get them back
where they came from.

1557
02:21:17.066 --> 02:21:19.705
No way to get them back. Thanos
destroyed the quantum tunnel.

1558
02:21:19.768 --> 02:21:20.869
Hold on!

1559
02:21:22.150 --> 02:21:24.478
That wasn't our
only time machine.

1560
02:21:30.419 --> 02:21:32.662
Anyone see an ugly
brown van up there?

1561
02:21:32.912 --> 02:21:33.692
Yes!

1562
02:21:33.739 --> 02:21:36.004
But you're not gonna
like where it's parked.

1563
02:21:36.029 --> 02:21:39.278
Scott. how long you need
to get that thing working?

1564
02:21:39.653 --> 02:21:40.853
Maybe ten minutes.

1565
02:21:40.857 --> 02:21:42.661
Get it started. We'll
get the stones to you.

1566
02:21:42.686 --> 02:21:44.193
We're on it. Cap.

1567
02:21:53.913 --> 02:21:54.913
Hey.

1568
02:21:55.233 --> 02:21:58.209
You said one out of 14
million. we win. yeah?

1569
02:21:59.255 --> 02:22:00.255
Tell me this is it.

1570
02:22:00.639 --> 02:22:03.904
If I tell you what
happens. it won't happen.

1571
02:22:07.567 --> 02:22:09.129
You better be right.

1572
02:22:16.918 --> 02:22:18.385
It's a mess back here.

1573
02:22:18.794 --> 02:22:21.208
It's... it's dead.

1574
02:22:21.395 --> 02:22:22.855
- What?
- It's dead.

1575
02:22:23.137 --> 02:22:24.762
I have to hotwire it.

1576
02:22:27.434 --> 02:22:28.935
Where's Nebula?

1577
02:22:29.583 --> 02:22:31.455
She's not responding.

1578
02:22:31.531 --> 02:22:32.531
Sire!

1579
02:22:42.536 --> 02:22:43.660
Clint!

1580
02:22:45.897 --> 02:22:47.091
Give it to me.

1581
02:23:09.398 --> 02:23:12.922
You took everything from me.

1582
02:23:13.047 --> 02:23:15.195
I don't even know who you are.

1583
02:23:15.586 --> 02:23:16.812
You will.

1584
02:23:39.361 --> 02:23:40.361
I got it!

1585
02:23:42.994 --> 02:23:44.657
Activate Instant Kill!

1586
02:24:08.052 --> 02:24:09.341
Rain fire!

1587
02:24:09.638 --> 02:24:11.887
But Sire. our troops!

1588
02:24:11.935 --> 02:24:13.192
Just do it!

1589
02:24:34.331 --> 02:24:35.948
Is anyone else seeing this?

1590
02:24:49.791 --> 02:24:50.869
I got this.

1591
02:24:51.072 --> 02:24:52.072
I got this!

1592
02:24:52.127 --> 02:24:53.439
Okay. I don't got this.

1593
02:24:53.447 --> 02:24:56.814
- Help! Somebody. help!
- Hey. Queens. Heads up.

1594
02:25:06.573 --> 02:25:08.440
Hang on. I got you. kid.

1595
02:25:11.361 --> 02:25:12.479
Hey! Nice to meet---

1596
02:25:12.501 --> 02:25:13.580
Oh! My God!

1597
02:25:50.987 --> 02:25:52.409
What the hell is this?

1598
02:25:52.799 --> 02:25:54.188
Friday. what are they firing at?

1599
02:25:54.213 --> 02:25:56.674
Something just entered
the upper atmosphere.

1600
02:26:09.471 --> 02:26:11.034
Oh. yeah!

1601
02:26:31.485 --> 02:26:33.915
Danvers. we need an assist here.

1602
02:26:42.556 --> 02:26:44.923
Hi. I'm Peter Parker.

1603
02:26:45.738 --> 02:26:48.924
Hey. Peter Parker. Got
something for me?

1604
02:26:54.559 --> 02:26:57.871
I don't know how you're
gonna get through all that.

1605
02:26:58.520 --> 02:26:59.699
Don't worry.

1606
02:27:00.676 --> 02:27:02.168
She's got help.

1607
02:29:49.812 --> 02:29:53.139
I am... inevitable.

1608
02:30:13.540 --> 02:30:14.618
And I...

1609
02:30:16.783 --> 02:30:17.993
am...

1610
02:30:21.657 --> 02:30:22.954
... Iron Man.

1611
02:32:19.706 --> 02:32:21.049
Mr. Stark?

1612
02:32:21.924 --> 02:32:22.924
Hey...

1613
02:32:24.080 --> 02:32:27.065
Mr. Stark? Can you hear me?

1614
02:32:27.110 --> 02:32:28.453
It's Peter.

1615
02:32:32.603 --> 02:32:34.063
We won.

1616
02:32:34.439 --> 02:32:35.439
Mr. Stark....

1617
02:32:37.462 --> 02:32:39.446
We won. Mr. Stark.

1618
02:32:40.984 --> 02:32:43.672
We won and you did it. sir.
You did it.

1619
02:32:45.273 --> 02:32:47.609
I'm sorry... Tony...

1620
02:33:01.182 --> 02:33:03.791
- Hey.
- Hey. Pep...

1621
02:33:08.428 --> 02:33:11.974
- Friday?
- Life functions critical.

1622
02:33:21.060 --> 02:33:22.146
Tony.

1623
02:33:23.458 --> 02:33:24.575
Look at me.

1624
02:33:27.099 --> 02:33:28.661
We're gonna be okay.

1625
02:33:33.739 --> 02:33:35.529
You can rest now.

1626
02:35:20.844 --> 02:35:23.383
Everybody wants a
happy ending. right?

1627
02:35:24.039 --> 02:35:26.439
But it doesn't always
roll that way.

1628
02:35:28.211 --> 02:35:29.570
Maybe this time.

1629
02:35:31.492 --> 02:35:34.085
I'm hoping if you
play this back.

1630
02:35:35.679 --> 02:35:37.421
it's in celebration.

1631
02:35:38.296 --> 02:35:40.501
I hope families are reunited.

1632
02:35:40.572 --> 02:35:42.806
I hope we get it back.
and something like a

1633
02:35:42.831 --> 02:35:45.312
normal version of the
planet has been restored.

1634
02:35:46.142 --> 02:35:48.524
If there ever was such a thing.

1635
02:35:48.790 --> 02:35:50.267
God. what a world.

1636
02:35:50.533 --> 02:35:52.243
Universe. now.

1637
02:35:52.900 --> 02:35:55.017
If you told me ten years
ago that we weren't alone.

1638
02:35:55.042 --> 02:35:56.540
let alone. you know.
to this extent.

1639
02:35:56.564 --> 02:36:00.165
I mean. I wouldn't have been surprised.
But come on. you know?

1640
02:36:00.494 --> 02:36:04.994
That epic forces of darkness and
light that have come into play.

1641
02:36:05.525 --> 02:36:07.192
And. for better or worse.

1642
02:36:07.356 --> 02:36:11.106
that's the reality Morgan's gonna
have to find a way to grow up in.

1643
02:36:15.000 --> 02:36:17.382
So I found the time and I
recorded a little greeting...

1644
02:36:17.470 --> 02:36:20.492
In the case of an untimely death.
On my part.

1645
02:36:20.813 --> 02:36:24.329
Not that. death in any
time isn't untimely.

1646
02:36:24.890 --> 02:36:27.278
This time travel thing that we're
gonna try and pull off tomorrow.

1647
02:36:27.303 --> 02:36:29.529
it's. it's got me scratching
my head about this.

1648
02:36:33.969 --> 02:36:37.352
But then again. that's the hero gig.
Part of the journey is the end.

1649
02:36:40.281 --> 02:36:44.437
Everything's gonna work out
exactly the way it's supposed to.

1650
02:36:47.730 --> 02:36:49.238
I love you 3.000.

1651
02:39:04.387 --> 02:39:06.504
You know. I wish
there was a way...

1652
02:39:06.598 --> 02:39:08.410
that I could let her know.

1653
02:39:10.394 --> 02:39:11.793
That we won.

1654
02:39:14.011 --> 02:39:15.253
We did it.

1655
02:39:19.269 --> 02:39:20.346
She knows.

1656
02:39:26.012 --> 02:39:27.291
They both do.

1657
02:39:36.958 --> 02:39:38.425
How you doing. Squirt?

1658
02:39:38.427 --> 02:39:40.513
- Good.
- You good?

1659
02:39:40.638 --> 02:39:43.372
- Okay. You hungry?
- Mm-hmm.

1660
02:39:43.919 --> 02:39:47.121
- What do you want?
- Cheeseburgers.

1661
02:39:51.813 --> 02:39:54.758
You know your Dad
liked cheeseburgers?

1662
02:39:58.313 --> 02:40:00.922
I'm gonna get you all the
cheeseburgers you want.

1663
02:40:00.938 --> 02:40:01.938
Okay.

1664
02:40:18.647 --> 02:40:22.382
So. when can we expect you back?

1665
02:40:24.695 --> 02:40:28.585
- About that...
- Thor. Your people need a king.

1666
02:40:28.700 --> 02:40:30.910
No. they already have one.

1667
02:40:32.731 --> 02:40:34.020
That's funny.

1668
02:40:39.091 --> 02:40:40.551
You're being serious?

1669
02:40:44.638 --> 02:40:46.920
It's time for me to be
who I am rather than

1670
02:40:47.505 --> 02:40:49.762
who I'm supposed to be.

1671
02:40:51.193 --> 02:40:55.098
But you. you're a leader.
That's who you are.

1672
02:40:57.751 --> 02:41:00.032
You know I'd make a lot
of changes around here.

1673
02:41:00.057 --> 02:41:03.236
I'm counting on it.
Your Majesty.

1674
02:41:13.295 --> 02:41:14.631
What will you do?

1675
02:41:15.014 --> 02:41:16.232
I'm not sure.

1676
02:41:16.873 --> 02:41:19.326
For the first time in a
thousand years. I...

1677
02:41:19.498 --> 02:41:22.146
I have no path. I do
have a ride. though.

1678
02:41:22.240 --> 02:41:24.466
Move it or lose it. hairbag.

1679
02:41:28.419 --> 02:41:29.950
Well. here we are.

1680
02:41:30.420 --> 02:41:32.607
Tree! Good to see you.

1681
02:41:34.841 --> 02:41:35.841
Well...

1682
02:41:36.699 --> 02:41:39.529
The As-Guardians of the
Galaxy back together again.

1683
02:41:40.571 --> 02:41:42.076
Where to first?

1684
02:41:45.114 --> 02:41:48.348
Just so you know. this is my ship still.
I'm in charge.

1685
02:41:48.691 --> 02:41:51.246
I know. I know. Of
course. you are.

1686
02:41:51.512 --> 02:41:52.723
Of course.

1687
02:41:55.294 --> 02:41:58.309
See. you say of course. but
then you touch the map.

1688
02:41:58.334 --> 02:42:01.216
It makes you think that maybe you
didn't realize I was in charge.

1689
02:42:01.318 --> 02:42:04.560
Quail. that's your own
insecurities in there. Okay?

1690
02:42:04.576 --> 02:42:06.770
I'm merely trying to be of service.
An assistant.

1691
02:42:06.795 --> 02:42:09.110
- Quill.
- That's what I said.

1692
02:42:09.135 --> 02:42:11.400
You should fight one another
for the honor of leadership.

1693
02:42:11.541 --> 02:42:12.970
Sounds fair.

1694
02:42:15.565 --> 02:42:17.252
- It's not necessary.
- It's not.

1695
02:42:17.268 --> 02:42:17.877
Okay?

1696
02:42:17.902 --> 02:42:20.542
I got some blasters unless
you guys wanna use knives.

1697
02:42:20.572 --> 02:42:23.064
Oh. yes. Please. use knives.

1698
02:42:23.947 --> 02:42:25.204
I am Groot.

1699
02:42:31.971 --> 02:42:32.971
Not necessary.

1700
02:42:33.018 --> 02:42:34.915
There shall be no
knifing one another.

1701
02:42:34.940 --> 02:42:37.549
Everybody knows who's in charge.

1702
02:42:41.213 --> 02:42:42.346
It's me.

1703
02:42:45.736 --> 02:42:48.635
Yes. you! Of course!

1704
02:42:49.002 --> 02:42:51.502
Of course. Of course.

1705
02:42:53.909 --> 02:42:54.994
Remember...

1706
02:42:56.375 --> 02:42:58.734
You have to return the stones at
the exact moment you got them.

1707
02:42:58.758 --> 02:43:02.422
Or you're gonna open up a bunch
of nasty alternative realities.

1708
02:43:02.484 --> 02:43:04.585
Don't worry. Bruce.
Clip all the branches.

1709
02:43:05.953 --> 02:43:07.437
You know. I tried.

1710
02:43:09.094 --> 02:43:12.812
When I had the gauntlet. the stones.
I really tried to bring her back.

1711
02:43:16.668 --> 02:43:19.910
- I miss them. man.
- Me. too.

1712
02:43:23.488 --> 02:43:26.457
You know. if you want.
I can come with you.

1713
02:43:28.740 --> 02:43:30.482
You're a good man. Sam.

1714
02:43:30.605 --> 02:43:32.651
This one's on me. though.

1715
02:43:36.566 --> 02:43:39.081
Don't do anything stupid
'till I get back.

1716
02:43:40.516 --> 02:43:43.711
How can I? You're taking
all the stupid with you.

1717
02:43:51.212 --> 02:43:52.742
Gonna miss you. Buddy.

1718
02:43:52.976 --> 02:43:54.836
It's gonna be okay. Buck.

1719
02:44:02.098 --> 02:44:04.191
How long is this gonna take?

1720
02:44:04.316 --> 02:44:07.112
For him? As long as he
needs. For us. five seconds.

1721
02:44:12.212 --> 02:44:13.462
